DESCRIPTION:<p>===========</p><p><u>This event is now <b>full and closed</b
 ></u>.&nbsp\; Thank you for your interest!&nbsp\; Please consider volunteer
 ing for the next Vancouver planting on Sat\, Jan 15th!</p><p>===========</p
 ><p>Let's plant trees together in SE Vancouver! Interested in receiving a t
 ree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b>
  to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees 
 will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes
  this community planting possible!<br></p><p><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to
  sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We
  provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress fo
 r the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and 
 be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help g
 etting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the
  central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftr
 ees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able t
 o help out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We re
 quest that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Yout
 h 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;
 <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></
 b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</
 b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several planting sites in 
 the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend
  private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely 
 able to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your participat
 ion\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safet
 y of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. W
 e are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with th
 e exception of those younger than 12 and anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompro
 mised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a fac
 e mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance fro
 m others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any o
 ther snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your house
 hold feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a h
 ref="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Ask
 ed Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.</p><p><b>Where will th
 ese trees be planted? </b>We will be planting in the following neighborhood
 s: Bella Vista\, Bennington\, Cascade Highlands\, Cascade Southeast\, East 
 Old Evergreen Highway\, Fairway/164th Ave\, Fisher's Creek\, Fisher's Landi
 ng East\, Lewis and Clark Woods\, Mountain View\, Northfield\, Riverridge\,
  Village at Fisher's Landing\, and Wildwood.</p><p>Please contact Jenny and
  Carey at <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u><
 /u>dsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any further information.
  We look forward to seeing you out there!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in
  partnership with the City of Vancouver Urban Forestry – thank you for your
  longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><i>Friends of Trees continue
 s to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Washingt
 on Department of Health &amp\; Human Services. If at any point we feel it i
 s not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers w
 ho are pre-registered.</i>\n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.co
 m/mqq-pwrg-vmk\nOr dial: (US) +1 470-705-3849 PIN: 607580568#\nMore phone n
 umbers: https://tel.meet/mqq-pwrg-vmk?pin=6373424597761&hs=7\n\nLearn more 
 about Meet at: https://support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
