 o help out in this key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that yo
 uth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can 
 volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsof
 trees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u><
 /u></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportatio
 n</b><span>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting si
 tes in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). </span><b>We recommen
 d private transportation</b><span> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an 
 option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortabl
 e with this. </span><br></p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In
  the following neighborhoods: <span>North Lancaster and East Lancaster.</sp
 an></p><p><b>Questions?  </b><span>Please check out our </span><a href="htt
 ps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ web
