UID:3lf78kfdr678nji25k9u2qt8qu@google.com
CREATED:20240821T215250Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>================================</b></p><p><b>Due to popu
 lar interest\, this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>.  Please consider o
 ur next Forest Grove planting event on Feb 1 at Stites Nature Park. </p><p>
 <b>=================================</b></p><p>Let's plant trees together i
 n Forest Grove! In April 2024\, several dozen trees infested by the Emerald
  Ash Borer were removed to slow the spread of the invasive beetle. This com
 munity tree planting event will replace trees removed due to the Emerald As
 h Borer to steward a resilient urban tree canopy in Forest Grove\, and your
  help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive b
 y 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at
  9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakf
 ast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress f
 or the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and
  be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 
 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunte
 er on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoft
 rees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u
 ></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportat
 ion</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites 
 in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private t
 ransportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool
  if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.<br><
 /p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach
  Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.
  We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><br><b><hr /></b><p>This
  event is in partnership with the Oregon Department of Forestry and funded 
 by the U.S. Forest Service.</p><p>Oregon Department of Forestry is an equal
  opportunity provider. Funding opportunity is provided by the USDA Forest S
 ervice - Federal Assistance Listing 10.727 Inflation Reduction Act (IRA) Ur
 ban and Community Forestry Grant Program</p>
