DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Online registration for this event is now closed.
  Registration is still available in-person at the planting.</p><p><br></p><
 p>Let's plant trees together in the North Lancaster neighborhood of NE Sale
 m! Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their n
 ew homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br
 ><br>Please arrive at McKay Park by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a pla
 nting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and 
 guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy sh
 oes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun! </p><p><
 br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer 
 with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their ow
 n and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/y
 outhwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian
 .</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting loc
 ation to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several m
 iles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike 
 or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If t
 his is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What 
 about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number 
 one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our e
 vents are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\
 , such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised
 \, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introdu
 ctions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own househ
 old\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you wil
 l need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two wee
 ks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/
 volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbs
 p\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questio
 ns?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team 
 is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny a
 t&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p>
 <b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Salem.</p><i>Fr
 iends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made 
 by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not s
 afe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are 
 pre-registered.</i></html-blob>
