DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b>Thanks to popular interest\, this trainin
 g is <u>full and closed</u></b>.  It's possible we'll host another training
  in early Winter.  If you'd like to be on the list for the next time we hol
 d this training\, please let us know!  volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</p><p>=
 ========</p><p>Would you like to help get more trees planted in the greater
 -Portland/Vancouver metro area while talking with people interested in the 
 same thing? Do you like learning about trees?  Are you open to connecting w
 ith people on the phone?  If so\, we have a volunteer role for you -- the <
 b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/canopy-cal
 ler/" target="_blank">Canopy Caller</a></b>!  </p><p>Canopy Callers connect
  with interested neighbors on the phone to help them find the right tree fo
 r their space and tastes\, as well as let them know how they can volunteer 
 at the planting event in their neighborhood. It’s a bit of community organi
 zing and a bit of customer service—all with the mission of increasing our u
 rban canopy!</p><p>Following the training\, we ask that you commit to four 
 (or more!) call nights (this role takes some time and practice to master). 
  You can join call nights at the office or remotely (if you’re willing to s
 et up Google Voice for free on your cell phone).  There are 2-3 call nights
  each month to choose from\, Sept-Feb. </p><p>Questions? Please connect wit
 h Cece and Jenny: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_bl
 ank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213.</p>
