CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive to the Holy Redeemer School at 8:45am for registr
 ation\, coffee\, and breakfast pastries. Enter from N Vancouver between sch
 ool and gym\, or from N Williams behind the church. Meet in Cantwell Hall (
 in the basement\, at NE corner of school). \n\n<b>Pre-registration is requi
 red for this training</b>\, please register <a href=http://www.friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteering/2012-08-29-17-44-58/summer-inspection-training>HERE</a>
  to save your spot!\n\nSummer inspectors are always one of our most popular
  volunteers roles. Why? These trained volunteers learn how to assess the he
 alth of newly planted street and yard trees and give homeowners watering an
 d mulching tips. Each inspector checks on his or her assigned trees twice d
 uring the summer (once in June and once in August). Being a summer inspecto
 r gives you a chance to meet your neighbors and to help them take care of t
 heir trees during the critical first summer after planting. Plus\, you get 
 to stroll around Portland's beautiful neighborhoods in the summer sun at yo
 ur own leisure. Not a bad way to do good work!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or R
 andi at 503-595-0213 or Volunteer@FriendsofTrees.org if you have any questi
 ons or need more information. We look forward to seeing you there!
