DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Oregon City! Interested in rec
 eiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"
  target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to pur
 chase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be
  ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this c
 ommunity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be
  assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves
 \, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/
 hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear stur
 dy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p>
 <p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, 
 but there is still room at this event!  Please simply show up and sign-in w
 hen you arrive.<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We have all the trucks n
 eeded for this event -- please consider signing-up for this role at a futur
 e neighborhood planting!<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 
 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volu
 nteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friends
 oftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</
 u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Pr
 ivate transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a fe
 w planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We re
 commend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an 
 option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortabl
 e with this.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>Volun
 teer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to as
 sist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoft
 rees.org" target="_blank"><b><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></
 u></u></u></b></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soo
 n!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Oregon 
 City.</p>
