DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><p>===========</p><p><b>Due to popular suppor
 t\, this event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Thank you for your
  interest -- please consider joining any other open event in the future!</p
 ><p>===========</p><p>Let's plant trees together in N Portland! Interested 
 in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tre
 e/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-
 10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your he
 lp is what makes this community planting possible!<br></p><p><br>Please arr
 ive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting star
 ts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all vol
 unteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind gett
 ing dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We 
 need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few bloc
 ks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http:/
 /www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> 
 if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;</p><p><b>This event 
 will have a bike crew!</b>&nbsp\;Want to join the team planting trees by bi
 ke? Sign up at&nbsp\;<b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/bike">www.fr
 iendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/bike</a></b>. Bikers with trailers and cargo bikes 
 are awesome but anyone with a bike is welcome to take part!&nbsp\;</p><p><b
 >Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with 
 a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and
  will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p>
 <p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location
  to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles)
 .&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or ve
 hicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this i
 s a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about
  Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one p
 riority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events
  are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, suc
 h as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, et
 c)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introduction
 s\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\,
  bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will nee
 d\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of
  this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;fo
 r more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will t
 hese trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborhoods: Cathedral 
 Park\, Linnton\, St Johns\, University Park\, Arbor Lodge\, Kenton\, Overlo
 ok\, and Portsmouth<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check o
 ut our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunte
 er FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You
  can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@f
 riendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look fo
 rward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partners
 hip with the City of Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – thank yo
 u for your longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><i>Friends of Tree
 s continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC an
 d Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host e
 vents\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registere
 d.</i><u></u><br><u></u><br><u></u><br><u></u>===<br>Thank you to our event
  sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="http://www.tree-source.net/">Rigert Shade Trees</a>
 !<br>===<i><br></i><u></u><br><u></u><i><br></i><u></u></html-blob>
