DESCRIPTION:<br><b>Registration is full and closed for the Beaverton Crew L
 eader Training. Please consider our training on <u>11/9 in Vancouver</u> or
  <u>11/23 in Gresham</u></b><br>==================<br><br><a href="https://
 friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"
 ><u><u>Planting C</u></u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/
 how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></a
 > are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading smal
 l group at our community planting events. Friends of Trees cannot run these
  events without the support of this valued position!  After your training\,
  we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Nov-April (
 select for events that fit your schedule!).    <br><br><u>This is an In-Per
 son training for new Crew Leaders in the Neighborhood Trees program.  Pleas
 e note: trainees will need to have completed the online training before the
 y attend this session</u>.  The online session will be sent to you and avai
 lable for two weeks.<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant different root sto
 cks\, learn about tree identification\, hone your inclusive leadership skil
 ls\, and meet the staff you'll be working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Plea
 se visit the <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer
 /crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u>Planting Crew Leader webpage</u></u></
 a> or contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank
 "><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></a>\, 503-595-0-213  We hope t
 o work with you in this important role!
