 h%2015\,%202025%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2025-03-15&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Sta
 ndard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sign u
 p</u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help out in this key ro
 le. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunte
 er with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own a
 nd will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwai
 ver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transpo
 rtation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting si
 tes in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend priva
 te transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to car
 pool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.<
 /p><p><b>Transit:</b> B<span>us Line 30 with a .1 mile walk.</span></p><p><
 b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ
  webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also hap
 py to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><b><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></b></a>\, 503-595-0213. We l
 ook forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in 
 partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
