UID:jclqmsoed3jtqsmmep246nv024@google.com
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive to the Holy Redeemer School at 8:45am for registr
 ation\, coffee\, and breakfast pastries. Enter from N Vancouver between sch
 ool and gym\, or from N Williams behind the church. Meet in Cantwell Hall (
 in the basement\, at NE corner of school). \n\nThis event is now full.  How
 ever\, if you'd like to be added to the Waitlist to become a Summer Inspect
 or\, please -- <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/friendsoftrees.org/spread
 sheet/viewform?usp=drive_web&formkey=dFkyYUkzaHB4b1NEMC1EMXNVWnNraXc6MA#gid
 =0">REGISTER HERE</a>\n\nSummer inspectors are always one of our most popul
 ar volunteers roles. Why? These trained volunteers learn how to assess the 
 health of newly planted street and yard trees and give homeowners watering 
 and mulching tips. Each inspector checks on his or her assigned trees twice
  during the summer (once in June and once in August).\n\nBeing a summer ins
 pector gives you a chance to meet your neighbors and to help them take care
  of their trees during the critical first summer after planting. Plus\, you
  get to stroll around Portland's beautiful neighborhoods in the summer sun 
 at your own leisure. Not a bad way to do good work. \n\nPlease contact Ian 
 or Jenny at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more informati
 on. We look forward to seeing you there!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:25 N Rosa Parks Way\, Portland\, OR\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Neighborhood Trees Summer Inspector Training (N Portland)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
