DESCRIPTION:In partnership with Oregon Walks\, Friends of Trees is hosting 
 a Tree Identification walk through the Montavilla neighborhood! Starting at
  Harrison Park School\, we will take a leisurely tour around the neighborho
 od\, visiting a variety of tree species Friends of Trees has planted over t
 he years. We will teach you how to identify different tree species by their
  branch\, bark\, and leaf patterns. \n\nMeet Haley and Megan near the entra
 nce to the Harrison Park School Community Garden on SE 87th at 6:00pm. The 
 walk will begin after a brief introduction and conclude back at the school 
 at 7:30pm. Contact Haley at Haleym@friendsoftrees.org or 503.465.2517 with 
 any questions! \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Harrison Park School\, 2225 SE 87th Ave\, Portland\, OR 97216\, US
 A\, Neighborhood Trees Events
