 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help 
 in this key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and 
 under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer o
 n their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees
 .org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transp
 ortation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting s
 ites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend priv
 ate transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to ca
 rpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.
  </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mailto:Voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><
