DESCRIPTION:~~~~~~~~~<br><br>Due to popular interest\, this training is now
  <b><u>full and closed</u></b>.  Please consider our next Crew Leader Train
 ing on Sat\, Jan 11th!<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~<br><br><a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>
 <u>Planting C</u></u></u></u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>rew Leaders<
 /u></u></u></u></a> are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting tree
 s and leading small group at our community planting events. Friends of Tree
 s cannot run these events without the support of this valued position!  Aft
 er your training\, we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning 
 events Nov-April (select for events that fit your schedule!).    <br><br><u
 >This is an In-Person training for new Crew Leaders in the Neighborhood Tre
 es program.  Please note: trainees will need to have completed the online t
 raining before they attend this session</u>.  The online session will be se
 nt to you and available for two weeks.<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant 
 different root stocks\, learn about tree identification\, hone your inclusi
 ve leadership skills\, and meet the staff you'll be working alongside!<br><
 br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 r/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>Planting Crew 
 Leader webpage</u></u></u></u></a> or contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org<
 /u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0-213  We hope to work with you in this impor
 tant role!<b><br><hr /></b><p>This event made possible through a grant from
  the USDA Forest Service. This institution is an equal opportunity provider
 .</p>
