DESCRIPTION:**Thank you for registering for this training\, due to the popu
 larity of this training we are now full\, hope to see you next year**\n\nCr
 ew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to plant trees properly a
 nd lead groups of volunteers at more than 80 different planting events this
  planting season.  Friends of Trees is aiming to plant more than 3\,000 str
 eet and yard trees in our award-winning Neighborhood Trees program.\n\nThe 
 November 11th training is taking place in Vancouver. We are hosting another
  training Crew Leader training in Portland\, OR on November 4th\, if that w
 orks better for your schedule. Curriculum for each training is the same and
  once completed\, you will be able to volunteer at Neighborhood Trees event
 s throughout Portland\, Vancouver\, Beaverton\, Gresham\, and Oregon City!\
 n\nThe training is free (and includes lunch and a t-shirt!) but registratio
 n is required. <b>Click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/
 2012-08-29-17-44-58/portland-vancouver-cl-training>HERE</a> to register for
  this popular training.</b>  Spots are limited and this training will fill-
 up so register soon! Location is in SE Portland and will be included with t
 he information sent upon your registration.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pabl
 o at (503) 595-0213 if you need more information. We look forward to answer
 ing any questions you may have!\n\n===\nThank you to our event sponsor\, <a
  href=http://www.tree-source.net/>Rigert Shade Trees</a>!\n===
