DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>==========</b></p><p><
 b>Thanks to popular interest\, this event is <u>full and closed</u>.  </b>P
 lease consider any other open stewardship event - we hope to work with you!
 </p><p><b>==========</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees together in Vancouver's
  Central-North neighborhoods (along the NE Fourth Plain corridor). </b><spa
 n>Interested in receiving a tree? Click </span><b><u><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></u></b><span> to purchase a tree for yo
 ur household. Several large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting i
 n their new homes\, at this small planting event.</span><br></p><p>Please a
 rrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting st
 arts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light
  breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. Following the event there w
 ill be a warm potluck lunch provided by the hosting neighborhood groups. We
  ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots yo
 u don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pick
 up truck?</b><span> We need your help getting these young trees to their pl
 anting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign u
 p at </span><b><u><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friends
 oftrees.org/truck</a></u></b><span> if you're able to help out in this key 
 role. </span></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under
  volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on the
 ir own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/
 youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.
 </p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting loca
 tion to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several mi
 les). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but th
 ere may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are a
 lso comfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone carpoo
 ling with others outside of their household wear a face mask\, and crack th
 e windows of the vehicle.  </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require
 </u> that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have
  been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of 
 the event.  We <u>recommend </u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and we
 ar a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical 
 distance. Please see our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 r-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</a></u></b> for more d
 etails.      </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the follow
 ing neighborhoods:  Bagley Downs\, <span>Fourth Plain Village\, </span><spa
 n>Green Meadows\, </span><span>Maplewood\, </span><span>Meadow Homes\, </sp
 an><span>Ogden\, </span><span>Vanmall\, </span><span>Walnut Grove\, and </s
 pan><span>West Minnehaha.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out 
 our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ
  webpage</a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gab
 riel and Jenny at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volun
 teer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b> We look forward to planting together so
 on!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://laughingpl
 anet.com/"><u><u><u><u>Laughing Planet</u></u></u></u></a> &amp\; <a href="
 https://www.timbers.com/">The Portland Timbers</a>.<br>===<br></p><p><br></
 p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of 
 Vancouver.<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
