DESCRIPTION:Treecology and Hoyt Arboretum are organizing an attempt to brea
 k the Guinness Book of World Records for the most people simultaneously hug
 ging trees in one place at one time. The current record is 935 people in Mi
 nnesota\, and we hope to smash that record!\n\nWe will gather in the Arbore
 tum near the intersection of Kingston and Knights Blvds. uphill from the Vi
 etnam War Memorial. Check-in begins at 2pm\, and the hug will take place ar
 ound 3pm.  Additional fun activities include tree-related information booth
 s\, a climbing wall\, Timber Joey\, Garry Oak and more!\n\nPARKING ALERT! P
 arking will be limited. Please consider alternative transportation includin
 g MAX\, tri-met bus #83\, biking and carpooling.\n\nA portion of t-shirt sa
 les will benefit Hoyt Arboretum Friends.\n\nQuestions? Please contact info@
 hoytarboretum.org.\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Hoyt Arboretum 
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hug A Tree At Hoyt - Break A World Record!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
