DESCRIPTION:<p>==========</p><p><b>This event is <u>full and closed</u></b>
 . Please consider any of our other available planting events. We hope to pl
 ant with you this Winter!</p><p>==========</p><p>Let's plant trees together
  in Outer SE Portland! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for y
 our household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for plantin
 g in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting 
 possible!<br></p><p><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned 
 a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\,
  and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear stur
 dy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p>
 <p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees 
 to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Pl
 ease sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friend
 softr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key
  role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 an
 d under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can vol
 unteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://fr
 iendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by the
 ir parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel fr
 om the meeting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhoo
 d (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportatio
 n</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpoo
 ling options. If this is a barrier to your participation\, please let us kn
 ow.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and st
 aff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that a
 ll people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those w
 ho are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely
  immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through
  the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not i
 n their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or
  beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unw
 ell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions w
 ebpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\
 ;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following ne
 ighborhoods: Lents\, Powelhurst-Gilbert\, Pleasant Valley\, and Centennial.
 <br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a 
 href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a><
 /b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\
 , Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">
 <b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting t
 ogether soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City o
 f Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – thank you for your longstan
 ding commitment to planting trees!</p><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to 
 follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health
  Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will
  cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><br>===<b
 r>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://wyldcanna.com/" id=
 "ow2596" __is_owner="true">WYLD</a>!<br>===<i><br></i><br><i><br></i>
