DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><b><br><hr><p></p></b><a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"><u>Planting C</u></a><a href
 ="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"><u>re
 w Leaders</u></a>&nbsp\;are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting 
 trees and leading small group at Friends of Trees community planting events
 . We can not run these events without the support of this valued position! 
 This training is for the Neighborhood Trees program where you'll plant larg
 e-stock (8-12' tall) trees in neighborhoods.<br><br><b><a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"><u>Learn more and 
 register here</u></a></b>&nbsp\;for this important position.&nbsp\;<u>Space
  limited\, but there is still space available and we welcome new registrant
 s until Mon\, 10/31</u>.</html-blob><br><html-blob><b style="background-col
 or: var(--textfield-surface)\; color: var(--on-surface)\;"><u><br></u></b><
 /html-blob><br><html-blob><ul><li><html-blob><b style="background-color: va
 r(--textfield-surface)\; color: var(--on-surface)\;"><u>A note on planting 
 location and personal transportation</u>:<u></u></b><span style="background
 -color: var(--textfield-surface)\; color: var(--on-surface)\;">&nbsp\;You w
 ill be eligible to Crew Lead at plantings in the following cities: Vancouve
 r\, Beaverton\, Cedar Mill\, NE Portland\, Gresham\, Milwaukie\, Oregon Cit
 y\, and Wilsonville (check out the purple events here on the online calenda
 r for more details). Personal transportation is recommended-- there will be
  an option to carpool during the event to your planting locations\, but we 
 cannot guarantee this as an option due to differing comfort levels of other
  FOT volunteers.</span></html-blob></li></ul><ul><li><b><u>What about Covid
 -19?</u></b>&nbsp\; Friends of Trees&nbsp\;<u>requires</u>&nbsp\;that all p
 eople at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed t
 o someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp
 \; We&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>every<u></u>one is fully-vaccinate<u></u
 >d\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respec
 t 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://frie
 ndsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions w
 ebpage</u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.</li></ul><b><p></p><hr><
 p></p></b>Ple<u></u>a<u></u>se contact Jenny or Gabriel if you need more in
 formation or have questions:&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org"><u>volu<u></u>nteer@frien<u></u>dsof<u></u>trees.org</u></a>. We look
  forward to working with you this planting season!</html-blob>
