DESCRIPTION:<p>======</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u>f
 ull and closed</u></b>. Please consider any of our other open events - we h
 ope to work with you soon!</p><p>======</p><p><span>Let's plant trees toget
 her in the Butternut Creek area! We will be planting large (6-10' tall) tre
 es at their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting
  possible!</span></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned 
 a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\,
  and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocol
 ate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/b
 oots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have
  a pickup truck?</b><span> We need your help getting these young trees to t
 heir planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. </span
 ><b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000IOB7G&tfa_21
 89=Butternut%20Creek%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0VPa000006fgkb&tfa_4
 5=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20March%2022\,%202025%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=
 2025-03-22&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank
 "><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></a></b><span> if you're able to help 
 out in this key role. </span></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that yo
 uth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can 
 volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://fri
 endsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u>
 </u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private tran
 sportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting
  sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend pr
 ivate transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to 
 carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with thi
 s.</p><p><b>Transit:</b> Bus Line 88 with a .1 mile walk.</p><p><b>Question
 s?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></a><
 /u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny a
 t <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></a></u></b> We look forward to
  planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a hr
 ef="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u>Portland General Elect
 ric</u></a> &amp\; <a href="https://www.nwnatural.com/" target="_blank"><u>
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>NW Natural</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.
 </p><p>===</p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p></p><p>This event is in partnershi
 p with Clean Water Services.</p>
