DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b>Due to popular community support\, this e
 vent is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any other open planting
  event -- we hope to work with you soon!</p><p>=========</p><p>Let's plant 
 trees together in Hillsboro!  Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to pur
 chase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be
  ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this c
 ommunity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be
  assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves
 \, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/
 hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear stur
 dy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p>
 <p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> Thanks to community support\, we're full for
  truck drivers for this event.  Please consider any of our other neighborho
 od-style plantings\, including Feb 21st in Cedar Hills / Cedar Mills!</p><p
 ><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a p
 arent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target
 ="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Priva
 te transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few p
 lanting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recom
 mend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an opt
 ion to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable w
 ith this. </p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https
 ://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mailto:Vo
 lunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look forward to working t
 ogether soon!<br><p><b>What neighborhoods will the trees be planted in?</b>
  Calle Diez + Downtown Hillsboro.</p><b><hr /></b><p></p><br><p>This event 
 made possible through a grant from the Arbor Day Foundation.</p>
