DESCRIPTION:<b>Due to popular interest\, this event is now full and closed 
 to further volunteer groups.</b>  Individuals and small groups of 4 or fewe
 r are welcome to simply show up!  Or please consider volunteering for our b
 iggest planting of the year in Westside Vancouver on Sat\, Feb 10th!\n\nPle
 ase arrive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some breakfast treats and
  hot coffee or chocolate. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provid
 e gloves and tools\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weath
 er and wearing sturdy shoes or boots. Our neighborhood volunteers will also
  provide a potluck lunch for all volunteers after the planting is complete.
  We're planting in the neighborhoods of Bagley Downs\, Burton Ridge\, Ellsw
 orth Springs\, Forest Ridge\, Marrion\, Meadow Homes\, Oakbrook\, Ogden\, a
 nd Vancouver Heights.    \n\nAre you under age 18 and planting without your
  parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/images/st
 ories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required for you to vol
 unteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an 
 adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny & Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have questi
 ons or need any further information. We look forward to seeing you out ther
 e!\n\n<i>Accessible on Bus Line 32.  For more directions\, visit <a href=ht
 tps://www.c-tran.com/>https://www.c-tran.com/</a>.</i>
