DESCRIPTION:===============================================================
 ==\n\n<b>Due to popular interest\, this planting is now FULL and closed to 
 additional group registrations of groups of 5 or more volunteers.</b> \n\n=
 ================================================================\n\nCelebra
 te Arbor Day with Friends of Trees and the City of Salem by planting a vari
 ety of native and ornamental trees at McKay Park. These new trees will help
  realize the parkâs recently completed master plan and will help to incre
 ase tree canopy cover in the North Lancaster Neighborhood. This event is th
 e final of many events in support of the Year of the Tree campaign\, celebr
 ating Salemâs 40th year as a Tree City USA. \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45
 am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly a
 t 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as
  gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and weari
 ng sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nPlease contact o
 ur Volunteer & Outreach Team at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or
  need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!\n\n<b>This
  planting is generously sponsored by PGE<b>\n\n
