DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>*****EVENT DELAYED UNTIL SAT\
 , MARCH 4th******</b></p><p>Due to snow\, Friends of Trees has made the dif
 ficult decision to <b><u>cancel and reschedule this event in Westside Vanco
 uver</u></b>.  Temperatures will remain mostly below freezing Thurs-Sat\, a
 nd we're concerned about road conditions as well as comfort planting in 25*
  weather.  Without snow substantially melting (which is unlikely)\, it will
  also be difficult to see the holes for planting the trees.  We're very sor
 ry for this change in plan!</p><p><b>If you are able\, please <a href="http
 s://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000P0u4A&tfa_2189=*Rescheduled:*
 %20Westside%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0V5G00000UajaG&tf
 a_45=Tree%20Planter\,%20%20at%20March%204\,%202023%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_219
 0=2023-03-04&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite">sign up her
 e</a> for the rescheduled event on Sat\, March 4th </b>or let our volunteer
  team know and they can transfer your registration: <a href="mailto:volunte
 er@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>. We appreciate the 
 support of our community!</p><br>******************************************
 ***********<p><span>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a pl
 anting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and
  guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate.
  Following the event there will be a warm potluck lunch provided by the hos
 ting neighborhood groups. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\
 , wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to ha
 ve fun!</span><br></p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b><span> We need your hel
 p getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from 
 the central staging site. Please sign up at </span><b><u><a href="http://ww
 w.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftrees.org/truck</a></u></b><span> 
 if you're able to help out in this key role. </span><br></p><p><b>Ride your
  bike?</b> There will be a bike planting crew at this event. Learn more and
  sign-up for the bike crew: <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/bike"><u><u
 >https://friendsoftrees.org/bike</u></u></a></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We 
 request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16
  and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a h
 ref="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b> s
 igned by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You wi
 ll travel from the meeting location to several planting sites in the nearby
  neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation
 </b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in
  your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. Please note: FOT 
 is requiring that anyone carpooling with others outside of their household 
 wear a face mask\, and crack the windows of the vehicle.  </p><p><b>What ab
 out Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> that all people at our events cancel if
  you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to someone who tested positive
  for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.  We <u>recommend </u>everyone is 
 fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarter
 s\, and respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our <b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions
  webpage</a></u></b> for more details.        </p><p><b>Where will these tr
 ees be planted? </b>In the following neighborhoods:  Arnada\, Carter Park\,
  Central Park\, Esther Short\, Fruit Valley\, Hough\, Hudson's Bay\, Lincol
 n\, Northwest\, Rose Village\, and Shumway.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please
  check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Vo
 lunteer FAQ webpage</a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You ca
 n reach Gabriel and Jenny at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b> We look forward to planting 
 together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https:/
 /wyldcanna.com/"><u><u><u>Wyld</u></u></u></a>.<br>===<br></p><p><br></p><b
 ><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p><
 u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>\n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.c
 om/gty-rcpo-kgx\nOr dial: (US) +1 937-589-2552 PIN: 202109679#\nMore phone 
 numbers: https://tel.meet/gty-rcpo-kgx?pin=5391678917428&hs=7\n\nLearn more
  about Meet at: https://support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
