DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in North Portland! Interested in 
 receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tre
 e/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a tre
 e for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for 
 planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community pl
 anting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a
  planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, 
 and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocola
 te. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/bo
 ots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How d
 o I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but there i
 s still room at this event! Please simply show up and sign-in when you arri
 ve.<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We are grateful to be full for this 
 role.  Please consider driving at a future neighborhood planting!</p><p><b>
 Want to plant by bike?</b> We're full for this role.  Please consider joini
 ng a future <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunte
 er/bike-planter/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>bike-powered crew</u></u></u></a
 ></b>.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volun
 teer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own
  and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></a></u></b> s
 igned by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You wi
 ll travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby n
 eighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</
 b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in y
 our small planting crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Questions?
   </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></a></u
 ></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at 
 <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u>volu
 nteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to
  planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p><br></p>
