DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Let's plant trees together in Oregon City! Intere
 sted in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-
 a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of larg
 e (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and yo
 ur help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arriv
 e by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts
  at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. Dress for the weather
 \, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to h
 ave fun! </p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at
  this time\, but there is still room at this event!&nbsp\; Please simply sh
 ow up\, and sign-in when you arrive - thanks!<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck
 ?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a
  few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a hre
 f="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck
 </a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>U
 nder age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a 
 parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and w
 ill need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwai
 ver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p
 ><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location t
 o several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&
 nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehi
 cle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this is 
 a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about C
 ovid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one pri
 ority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events a
 re fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such 
 as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)
 <b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\
 , respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, b
 ring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\
 , and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of t
 his event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunte
 er-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for 
 more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will the
 se trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following South Oregon City neighborh
 oods: Gaffney Lane\, Hazel Grove - Westling Farm\, Hillendale\, and Tower V
 ista.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<
 b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gab
 riel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.
 org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to plant
 ing together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the C
 ity of Oregon City.</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelin
 es and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at a
 ny point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and no
 tify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i></html-blob>
