DESCRIPTION:Registration for this Crew Leader Training is now closed. Pleas
 e consider joining us at any of our planting events or for our Green Space 
 Crew Leader training in January! <br><br>----------------------------------
 -----------------------<br><br><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>Planting C<
 /u></u></u></u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-vol
 unteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></u></u
 ></a></b> are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and lead
 ing small group at our community planting events. Friends of Trees cannot r
 un these events without the support of this valued position!  After your tr
 aining\, we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Nov
 -April (select for events that fit your schedule!).  <b><br></b><br>  <br><
 u>This is an In-Person training for new Crew Leaders in the Neighborhood Tr
 ees program.  Please note: trainees will need to have completed the online 
 training before they attend this session</u>.  The online training will be 
 emailed to you\, and you'll have two weeks to complete it before this in-pe
 rson training.<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant different root stocks\, 
 learn about tree identification\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, a
 nd meet the staff you'll be working alongside. Lunch provided\, as well as 
 a "Tree Team" tshirt!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank">
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><b>Planting Crew Leader webpage</b></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></a> or contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_b
 lank"><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></a>\, 503-595-0213  We look forwa
 rd to working with you in this important role!
