DESCRIPTION:========<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u>f
 ull and closed</u></b>.  The next Salem event is Sat\, Dec 7th at Woodmanse
 e Park (S Salem).  Perhaps we'll see you there\, or at another future plant
 ing?<br><br>========<br><br>50 large stock trees (6-10' tall) will be ready
  at this event for planting in their forever homes. These trees will bring 
 long-term human and environmental health benefits to this popular park and 
 the nearby area. Park parking can fill up\, please give yourself a little e
 xtra time and carpool/take public transit if you're able! We appreciate you
  for committing to help make this corner of the world a happier\, healthier
  place!<p>Please arrive by 11:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting cr
 ew. The planting starts at 12:00pm. We provide gloves\, tools\, and plantin
 g guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- al
 l you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or
  boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We reques
 t that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and o
 lder can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="h
 ttp://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.<br>
 </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You
  can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" 
 target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@f
 riendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!</p>
