UID:7cqc97da2u6t0plvacif8qqssh@google.com
CREATED:20210819T214307Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>===============</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this even
 t is now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; We hope you consider joining th
 e tree-planting fun at a future Beaverton planting on Dec 4th or Dec 11th\,
  or at any other open planting event.&nbsp\; Thank you!</p><p>=============
 ==</p><p>Let's plant trees together in Beaverton in the Southridge neighbor
 hood! Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in thei
 r new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!
 <br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew.
  The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. W
 e ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots y
 ou don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 
 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/gu
 ardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need 
 to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">yout
 h waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What 
 about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number 
 one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our e
 vents are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 12and 
 anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b
 >\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, 
 respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bri
 ng your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, 
 and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of thi
 s event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer
 -faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for mo
 re details.</p><p>Please contact Jenny and Carey at <a href="mailto:volunte
 er@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a> if you have 
 questions or need any further information. We look forward to seeing you ou
 t there!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Bea
 verton – thank you for your longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><
 i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations m
 ade by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is n
 ot safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who 
 are pre-registered.</i>
