DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in North Portland! Interested in 
 receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tre
 e/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' ta
 ll) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is 
 what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am 
 to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. 
 We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snack
 s and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the we
 ather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready
  to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has close
 d at this time\, but there is still room at this event. Please simply show-
 up and sign in at the welcome table!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request 
 that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and old
 er can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="htt
 p://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>yo
 uth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their par
 ent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the
  meeting location to a few plantingsites in the nearby neighborhood (up to 
 several miles). <b>We recommendprivate transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)
 \, but there may be an optionto carpool if others in your small planting cr
 ew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check o
 ut our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and J
 enny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a
 >\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p><b>What 
 neighborhoods will the trees be planted in?</b> East Columbia\, Kenton\, Pi
 edmont\, Portsmouth\, St Johns\, and Woodlawn.</p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to
  our event sponsor\, <a href="https://www.honltreecare.com/" target="_blank
 "><u><u>Honl Tree Care</u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p
 ></p><p>This event is in partnership with Portland Urban Forestry.</p>
