DESCRIPTION:<p><b>==========</b></p><p><b>This event is full and closed.</b
 > Please consider another open event before the end of our 23-24 event seas
 on in May.  Thank you!</p><p><b>==========</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees t
 ogether along Fourth Plain Boulevard! </b>Interested in receiving a tree? C
 lick <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> to purchase a tree for your h
 ousehold. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in 
 their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possi
 ble!<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am on the South side of Bagley Communit
 y Park to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9
 :00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfas
 t snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for
  the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and b
 e ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help ge
 tting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the 
 central staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a
 0T5G00000fQk9Z&tfa_2189=Central%2DNorth%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planti
 ng&tfa_31=a0V5G00000W2cji&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20April%2013\,%20
 2024%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-04-13&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT
 &tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></
 u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help out in this key role. <br></p
 ><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with 
 a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will 
 need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_
 blank"><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> sign
 ed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b><span>: You
  will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearb
 y neighborhood (up to several miles). </span><b>We recommend private transp
 ortation</b><span> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpoo
 l if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. </s
 pan><br></p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the following n
 eighborhoods: <span>Bagley Downs\, </span><span>Fourth Plain Village\, </sp
 an><span>Green Meadows\, </span><span>Maplewood\, </span><span>Meadow Homes
 \, </span><span>Ogden\, </span><span>Vanmall\, </span><span>Walnut Grove\, 
 and </span><span>West Minnehaha.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please che
