DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><p>===========</p><p><b>Due to 
 popular interest\, this event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please con
 sider any of other available planting -- thank you for your support! We'll 
 be planting in West Gresham on March 19th and would love to work with you t
 hen!<br></p><p>===========</p><p>Let's plant trees together in East Portlan
 d! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees
 .org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozen
 s of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes
 \, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Ple
 ase arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planti
 ng starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that 
 all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mi
 nd getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?<
 /b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a f
 ew blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href=
 "http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</
 a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Und
 er age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a pa
 rent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and wil
 l need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaive
 r">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><
 b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to 
 several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nb
 sp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicl
 e)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this is a 
 barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Cov
 id-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one prior
 ity at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are
  fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as
  children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b
 >\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, 
 respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bri
 ng your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, 
 and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of thi
 s event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer
 -faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for mo
 re details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these
  trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborhoods: Glenfair\, Haz
 elwood\, Mill Park\, Argay\, Parkrose\, Parkrose Heights\, Russell\, Wilkes
 \, and Woodland Park.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check
  out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volun
 teer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; Y
 ou can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer
 @friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look 
 forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in pa
 rtnership with the City of Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – th
 ank you for your longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><i>Friends o
 f Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the 
 CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to 
 host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-reg
 istered.</i><i><br></i><u></u><br><u></u>===<br>Thank you to our event spon
 sors&nbsp\;<a href="https://wyldcanna.com/">Wyld</a>\,&nbsp\;<a href="https
