CREATED:20240817T031659Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Westside Vancouver neighborhoo
 ds! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></
 u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10
 ' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help
  is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:4
 5am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00
 am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast s
 nacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for th
 e weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be r
 eady to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Pre-registration has clos
 ed at this time\, but there is still room at this event! Please simply show
 -up at 8:45am and sign-in at the welcome table.<b><br></b></p><p><b>Want to
  plant by bike?</b> Pre-registration has closed at this time\, but there is
  still room on the bike crew!  Please simply show-up at 8:45am\, and sign-i
 n at the welcome table (tell us you want the bike crews).</p><p><b>Have a p
 ickup truck?</b> This role is full for this event.  Please consider driving
  at the next Vancouver planting on Sat\, March 15th!</p><p><b>Under age 18?
 </b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  
 Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b
 ><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><
 u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their p
 arent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from t
 he meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up 
 to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehi
 cle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planti
 ng crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Transit:</b><span> Bus Lin
 e 71 with a .3 mile walk.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out 
 our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blan
 k"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  O
 ur team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="
 mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>volunte
 er@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnersh
 ip with the City of Vancouver.</p>
