DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p>======</p><p><b>Due t
 o popular support\, this event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Th
 ank you to everyone already signed-up -- you're making this biggest plantin
 g of the year a big success!&nbsp\; Not already sigend-up? Please consider 
 our next Vancouver planting on Sat\, March 26th (or any other open planting
 ). Thank you!</p><p>======</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be 
 assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, 
 wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have
  fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these you
 ng trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging
  site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">w
 ww.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in
  this key role.&nbsp\;</p><p><b>This event will have a bike crew!</b>&nbsp\
 ;Want to join the team planting trees by bike? Sign up at&nbsp\;<b><a href=
 "http://www.friendsoftrees.org/bike">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/bike</a>
 </b>. Bikers with trailers and cargo bikes are awesome but anyone with a bi
 ke is welcome to take part!&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 
 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>
 &nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>
 : You will travel from the meeting location to several planting sites in th
 e nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend p
 rivate transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely ab
 le to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your participatio
 n\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety 
 of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We 
 are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the 
 exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, a
 nyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear
  a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distan
 ce from others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and
  any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your
  household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp
 \;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequent
 ly Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &
 nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b
 >In the following neighborhoods: Arnada\, Carter Park\, Central Park\, Esth
 er Short\, Fourth Plain Village\, Fruit Valley\, Hough\, Hudson's Bay\, Lin
 coln\, Northwest\, Rose Village\, Shumway\, and West Minnehaha.<br></p><p><
 b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; 
 Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, an
 d Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer
 @friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon
 !<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Vancou
 ver Urban Forestry – thank you for your longstanding commitment to planting
  trees!</p><p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and re
 commendations made by the CDC and Washington Department of Health &amp\; Hu
 man Services. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we wi
 ll cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i></p><p>
 ===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://wyldcanna.com/
 ">Wyld</a>!<br>===<i><br></i></p><p><i><br></i></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u>
 </u></html-blob>\n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.com/jrv-iqjx
 -boi\nOr dial: (US) +1 669-244-0173 PIN: 165597611#\nMore phone numbers: ht
 tps://tel.meet/jrv-iqjx-boi?pin=4435796721994&hs=7\n\nLearn more about Meet
  at: https://support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
