DESCRIPTION:<b>UPDATE: Due to weather and freezing site conditions forecast
 ed through the weekend\, this planting is postponed until further notice. W
 e apologize for any inconvenience and thank you for your flexibility!</b> I
 f you have questions please contact us at volunteer@friendsoftrees.org.\n\n
 Canceling an event is a bummer. The good news is we have several planting e
 vents next weekend on Saturday\, January 21st. Feel free to take a look at 
 those events and let us know if you'd like to attend!\n\n==\n\nPlease arriv
 e at Mt. Scott Learning Center by 8:45am to find parking\, join a planting 
 crew\, and enjoy some hot coffee and breakfast treats. The planting starts 
 promptly at 9:00am. \n\nWe provide gloves and tools\, so all you need to do
  is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes. Our neighborh
 ood volunteers will also provide a potluck lunch for all volunteers after t
 he planting is complete!\n\nPlease contact Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 
 if you have questions or need any further information.\n\nWe look forward t
 o seeing you out there!
