DESCRIPTION:<p>======</p><p><b><u>Due to popular interest\, this event is f
 ull for planter volunteers but we still need truck drivers</u></b>. </p><p>
 <b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to 
 their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. <b><a
  href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000qajaO&tfa_2189=Cen
 tral-South%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting\,%20Vancouver&tfa_31=a0VPa
 000008zJZ4&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20November%2015\,%202025%20at%20
 8:30%20am&tfa_2190=2025-11-15&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offs
 ite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help in this key role. </p><p>==
 ====</p><p>Let's plant trees together in Central-South Vancouver! Dozens of
  large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, a
 nd your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please a
 rrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting st
 arts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light
  breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers 
 dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirt
 y\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that yo
 uth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can 
 volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://fri
 endsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form<
 /u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Priva
 te transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few p
 lanting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recom
 mend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an opt
 ion to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable w
 ith this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="htt
 ps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>Volunte
 er FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assi
 st!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftre
 es.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u
 ></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>
 <b>What neighborhoods will the trees be planted in?</b> Central Park\, Colu
 mbia River\, Dubois Park\, Edgewood Park\, Ellsworth Springs\, Evergreen Hi
 ghlands\, Evergreen Shores\, Forest Ridge\, Harney Heights\, Hudsons Bay\, 
 Marrion\, North Garrison Heights\, Northcrest\, Northwood\, Riverview\, Sou
 thcliff\, and Vancouver Heights.</p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to our event spo
 nsor\, <a href="https://www.bartlett.com/" target="_blank"><u><u>Bartlett T
 ree Experts</u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p></p><p>This event is 
 in partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
