DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>Let's plant trees 
 together in Salem!&nbsp\;</b>Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be rea
 dy for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this commu
 nity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be ass
 igned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, t
 ools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot 
 chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy s
 hoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><
 b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed\, but there is stil
 l room at this event! Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive!</p
 ><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer
  with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their o
 wn and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.or
 g/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/g
 uardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> that all peopl
 e at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to so
 meone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; W
 e <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a fa
 ce mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical distanc
 e. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer
