DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and the City of Salem in planting large s
 tock oak trees at Royal Oaks Park to help it live up to its name. We will a
 lso be planting a few additional species as well in this NE Salem park all 
 in an effort to increase tree canopy cover across NE neighborhoods. This ev
 ent is one of many events in support of the Year of the Tree campaign\, cel
 ebrating Salemâs 40th year as a Tree City USA.\n\n<b>Please note: this pl
 anting is now full and closed to groups of 5 or more people.</b>  Individua
 ls and small groups are still welcome to sign-up using our <a href=https://
 docs.google.com/a/friendsoftrees.org/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSckmLFnBY1hrjARDewGXp
 Mw1KdoJ4VQb3APcikSkekzZ8HYYw/viewform?formkey=dGhGNTNlbzJwQ3hibHZaVkNtUWVYN
 Gc6MA>Salem Planter Sign-Up Form.</a>\n\nAll planters should arrive around 
 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start prompt
 ly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as wel
 l as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and w
 earing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nAny question
 s at all?  Please contact Randi and Jenny in our Volunteer & Outreach Progr
 am: (503) 595-0213\, Volunteer@FriendsofTrees.org.  We look forward to plan
 ting with you!
