DESCRIPTION:<p>==========</p><p><b>Due to popular community interest\, this
  event is <u>full and closed</u></b>.  Please consider any of our other ope
 n event.</p><p>==========</p><p><span>Let's plant trees together in NE Vanc
 ouver! Interested in receiving a tree? Click </span><b><u><a href="https://
 friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b><span> to purchase a tree for your ho
 usehold. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in t
 heir new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possib
 le!</span></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a plant
 ing crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and gu
 idance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We
  ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots yo
 u don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pick
 up truck?</b><span> We need your help getting these young trees to their pl
 anting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. </span><b><a 
 href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000IOB7L&tfa_2189=Nort
 heast%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0VPa0000042XCL&tfa_45=T
 ruck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20April%2012\,%202025%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=202
 5-04-12&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b><span
 > if you're able to help out in this key role. </span></p><p><b>Under age 1
 8?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.
   Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a 
 <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> s
 igned by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You wi
 ll travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby n
 eighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</
 b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in y
 our small planting crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Questions?
   </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You 
 can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" t
 arget="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together 
 soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://www.nwna
 tural.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>NW Natural</u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in part
 nership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
