DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/
 crew-leader/">Crew Leaders</a> are trained volunteers who are crucial to pl
 anting trees properly and leading groups of volunteers from the public at m
 ore than 25 planting events this coming planting season. Friends of Trees i
 s aiming to plant more than 3\,000 street and yard trees in our Neighborhoo
 d Trees Program\, and we can't do it without your help!<br><br>The November
  2nd training is taking place in SE Portland. We have another Crew Leader t
 raining in Vancouver\, WA on November 9th if that works better for your sch
 edule. Curriculum for each training is the same and once completed\, you wi
 ll be able to volunteer at Neighborhood Trees events throughout Portland\, 
 Vancouver\, Beaverton\, Gresham\, Oregon City\, and Wilsonville!<br><br>Ple
 ase contact Jenny or Pablo if you need more information: 503-595-0213 // <a
