CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:A slide show presentation showcasing the trees that Friends of 
 Trees is offering this year followed by Q&A session with one of Portland's 
 best local tree experts\, Jim Gersbach.\n\nThis presentation is FREE and li
 ght refreshments will be provided. \n\nOur presenter\, Jim Gersbach\, has v
 olunteered in many\, many capacities with Friends of Trees for almost two d
 ecades now. Jim has an incredible range of knowledge about Portland's urban
  forest--from how different species tolerate our specific urban climate to 
 what trees grow where across the city.  Further\, he has been inspired to t
 ravel far and wide to visit noteworthy trees across the country and beyond.
 \n\nHe is also the visionary behind the Ainsworth Linear Arboretum that run
 s for nearly 2 miles along NE Ainsworth St. from MLK Blvd. to Fernhill Park
 .  As a labor of love\, Jim has not only planted dozens of rare and unusual
  trees here\, but he has hand watered them\nthrough many a hot summer.  He 
 leads tours of the Linear Aboretum seasonally\, which are advertised throug
 h Friends of Trees' Growth Rings blog and Portland Parks and Recreation's T
 reeBark e-newsletter. \n\nThere is no time like the present to order trees 
 for the upcoming Friends of Trees Planting Day in YOUR neighborhood!  Every
  year we sell out of a number of tree species\, so purchase your top picks 
 as soon as possible.  If you need assistance in making a selection\, but ca
 nnot make this presentation\, give us a call at 503-282-8846.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:St. Johns Community Center\, 8427 N Central St\, Portland\, OR 972
 03
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tree Selection Presentation with Jim Gersbach
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
