DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Vancouver! Interested in recei
 ving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" t
 arget="_blank"><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a t
 ree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready fo
 r planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community 
 planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned
  a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\
 , and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot choco
 late. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/
 boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How
  do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but there
  is still room at this event!  Please simply show up and sign-in when you a
 rrive.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volun
 teer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own
  and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></u
 ></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>:
  You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the n
 earby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transport
 ation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if othe
 rs in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Que
 stions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org
 /volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></
 u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can rea
 ch Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="
 _blank"><b><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u><
 /b></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><h
 r /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
