CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive to the Montavilla United Methodist Church (Fellow
 ship Hall) at 8:45am for registration\, coffee\, and breakfast pastries. \n
 \nThis event is now full.  However\, if you'd like to be added to the Waitl
 ist to become a Summer Inspector\, please -- <a href="https://docs.google.c
 om/a/friendsoftrees.org/spreadsheet/viewform?usp=drive_web&formkey=dFkyYUkz
 aHB4b1NEMC1EMXNVWnNraXc6MA#gid=0">REGISTER HERE</a>\n\nSummer inspectors ar
 e always one of our most popular volunteers roles. Why? These trained volun
 teers learn how to assess the health of newly planted street and yard trees
  and give homeowners watering and mulching tips. Each inspector checks on h
 is or her assigned trees twice during the summer (once by the end of June a
 nd once by the end of August). \n\nBeing a summer inspector gives you a cha
 nce to meet your neighbors and to help them take care of their trees during
  the critical first summer after planting. Plus\, you get to stroll around 
 Portland's beautiful neighborhoods in the summer sun at your own leisure. N
 ot a bad way to do good work. \n\nPlease contact Ian or Jenny at (503) 595-
 0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to
  seeing you there!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:232 Southeast 80th Avenue\, Portland\, OR 97215\, United States
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Neighborhood Trees Summer Inspector Training (SE Portland)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
