DESCRIPTION:Due to the extreme cold weather of the past two weeks\, we were
  unable to plant all of the 350 trees planned for last Saturday's planting 
 events in 6 different SE Portland neighborhoods. We still have about 55 tre
 es to plant and need to get them in the ground in the next week!\n\nWe are 
 organizing a special planting <b>this Saturday\, December 14th from 9:00am 
 - 12:30pm</b> and we need planting volunteers to help make it happen!\n\nWe
 'll have hot coffee and breakfast treats to get you started and we'll provi
 de gloves\, tools and trained guidance. No experience is necessary. Simply 
 show up around 8:45am at the west end of Creston Park (follow the Friends o
 f Trees signs). Thank you!\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Creston Park\, SE 44th Avenue and SE Powell Blvd. Portland OR
