DESCRIPTION:Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting
  trees properly and leading groups of volunteers at more than 25 planting e
 vents this coming planting season!&nbsp\; Friends of Trees is aiming to pla
 nt more than 3\,000 street and yard trees in our award-winning Neighborhood
  Trees program\, and we can't do it without your help!<br><br>The November 
 3rd training is taking place in NE Portland. We have another Crew Leader tr
 aining in Vancouver\, WA on November 10th\, if that works better for your s
 chedule. Curriculum for each training is the same and once completed\, you 
 will be able to volunteer at Neighborhood Trees events throughout Portland\
 , Vancouver\, Beaverton\, Gresham\, and Oregon City!<br><br>The training is
  free (and includes lunch and a t-shirt!) but registration is required.&nbs
 p\; Register <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/portland-vancouver-crew-le
 ader-training/" target="_blank">HERE</a> to save your spot at this popular 
 event.&nbsp\; Spots are limited and this training will fill-up so <a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/portland-vancouver-crew-leader-training/" target
 ="_blank">register now!</a><br><br>Please contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 5
 95-0213 if you need more information. We look forward to answering any ques
 tions you may have!
