 .friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">website</a> for additional details. If
  you were expecting to receive a tree tomorrow\, please expect an email fro
 m your planting lead on the status and plan for your tree(s).<br><br>We fac
 tor in a number of things when it comes to moving forward or canceling an e
 vent\, but your safety is our top priority. We apologize for any inconvenie
 nce this causes you and appreciate your patience and understanding as we so
 rt through this unexpected bump in the road!<br><br><br>**********<br>Due t
 o popular interest\, this event is now<b> FULL and CLOSED </b>to more volun
 teers.&nbsp\; Please consider our NE Vancouver and Clark County events in t
 he coming weeks!<br><br>**********<br><br><u><br></u><i>Neighborhoods inclu
 de: Arnada\, Carter Park\, Edgewood Park\, Fourth Plain Village\, Fruit Val
 ley\, Hough\, Hudson's Bay\, Lincoln\, Northwest\, Rose Village\, and Shumw
 ay.<br></i><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast 
 snacks and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts promptly at
  9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do i
 s show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â and
