CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive to the Vancouver City Hall at 8:45am for registra
 tion\, coffee\, and breakfast pastries.  \n\n<strong>Due to popular demand\
 , this training is now full and closed. </strong>\n\nSummer inspectors are 
 always one of our most popular volunteers roles. Why? These trained volunte
 ers learn how to assess the health of newly planted street and yard trees a
 nd give homeowners watering and mulching tips. Each inspector checks on his
  or her assigned trees twice during the summer (once in June and once in Au
 gust). Being a summer inspector gives you a chance to meet your neighbors a
 nd to help them take care of their trees during the critical first summer a
 fter planting. Plus\, you get to stroll around Portland's beautiful neighbo
 rhoods in the summer sun at your own leisure. Not a bad way to do good work
 !\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at 503-595-0213 or Volunteer@FriendsofTr
 ees.org if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward
  to seeing you there!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
