DTSTART:20230325T154500Z
DTEND:20230325T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260313T023243Z
UID:3j0bjmg6aq1g62gnrv4fb9r4uv@google.com
CREATED:20220829T180116Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>This event is <u>closed to online re
 gistration\, you can still sign-up in person on Saturday at our registratio
 n table! </u></b><br></p><p><br></p><p><b>Let's plant trees together in NE 
 Vancouver neighborhoods! </b>Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></u></b> to purchase
  a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be read
 y for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this commun
 ity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assi
 gned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, to
 ols\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot c
 hocolate. Following the event there will be a warm potluck lunch provided b
 y the hosting neighborhood groups. We ask that all volunteers dress for the
  weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be re
 ady to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b><span>Register by filling 
 out </span><b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000Vb
 lkl&tfa_2189=NE%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0V5G00000UWj8
 o&tfa_45=Tree%20Planter\,%20%20at%20March%2025\,%202023%20at%208:45%20am&tf
 a_2190=2023-03-25&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite">this q
 uick form</a></b><span>.  Groups and individuals welcome! If your group is 
 more than 5 people\, please know you will be assigned to different planting
  crews.</span></p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting 
 these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the centra
 l staging site. Please sign up at <b><u><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.
 org/truck">www.friendsoftrees.org/truck</a></u></b> if you're able to help 
 out in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15
  and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunt
 eer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsof
 trees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b> signed by their parent
 /guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the me
 eting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to 
 several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle
 )\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting 
 crew are also comfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that any
 one carpooling with others outside of their household wear a face mask\, an
 d crack the windows of the vehicle.  </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We 
 <u>require</u> that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwe
 ll or have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 
 3 days of the event.  We <u>recommend </u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, br
 ing and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of
  physical distance. Please see our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</a></u></b> 
 for more details.        </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>I
 n the following neighborhoods: Airport Green\, Parkside\, Burnt Bridge Cree
 k\, Countryside Woods\, First Place\, Image\, Landover Sharmel\, and North 
 Image.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></u></b>.  Our
  team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at <b><u><a
  href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a
 ></u></b> We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you
  to our event sponsors <a href="https://laughingplanet.com/"><u><u>Laughing
  Planet</u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partners
 hip with the City of Vancouver.<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u>
