DESCRIPTION:===========<br><br><b><u>Due to popular interest\, this trainin
 g is now full and closed</u></b>. There is still a little space at our Sat\
 , Nov 1st Beaverton training - we hope to see you there!<br><br><br>=======
 ====<br><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/c
 rew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>Planting C</u></u></u></u></u><
 /a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-lead
 er/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></u></u></u></a></b>
  are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading small
  group at our community planting events. Friends of Trees cannot run these 
 events without the support of this valued position!  After your training\, 
 we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Nov-April (s
 elect for events that fit your schedule!).    <br><u><br></u><u>This is an 
 In-Person training for new Crew Leaders in the Neighborhood Trees program. 
  Please note: trainees will need to have completed the online training befo
 re they attend this session</u>.  The online training will be emailed to yo
 u\, and you'll have two weeks to complete it before this in-person training
 .<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn about t
 ree identification\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet the s
 taff you'll be working alongside. Lunch provided\, as well as a "Tree Team"
  tshirt!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="https://friendsoftrees
 .org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><
 u><b>Planting Crew Leader webpage</b></u></u></u></u></u></a> or contact: <
 a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213  We look forward to working with you in t
 his important role!
