DESCRIPTION:Overwhelmed by the choices? Let our Tree Matching Expert\, Jim 
 Gersbach help you find your "soil"mate. The right tree is out there\, let u
 s help you find it.\n\nJim will be helping N and NE Portland and Vancouver 
 neighbors find their perfect tree. The presentation is free\, and light ref
 reshments will be provided. \n\nOregon Public House will also be open to pr
 ovide any additional food and beverage needs.\n\nJim is a long-time Friends
  of Trees volunteer and will share information\, photos and fun facts about
  the trees FOT is offering this year. Jim has an incredible range of knowle
 dge about Portland's urban forest--from how different species tolerate our 
 specific urban climate to what trees grow where across the city. \n\nFurthe
 r\, he has been inspired to travel far and wide to visit noteworthy trees a
 cross the country and beyond.\n\nHe is also the visionary behind the Ainswo
 rth Linear Arboretum that runs for nearly 2 miles along NE Ainsworth St. fr
 om MLK Blvd. to Fernhill Park. As a labor of love\, Jim has not only plante
 d dozens of rare and unusual trees here\, but he has hand watered them thro
 ugh many a hot summers. \n\nThere is no time like the present to order tree
 s for the upcoming Friends of Trees Planting Day in YOUR neighborhood! \n\n
 Every year we sell out of a number of tree species\, so log-in at FriendsOf
 Trees.org to select and order your top picks as soon as possible! \n\nIf yo
 u need assistance in making a selection\, but cannot make this presentation
 \, give us a call at 503-595-0212.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Oregon Public House (700 NE Dekum St) - upstairs in the Village Ba
 llroom
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Speed (Tree) Dating â Find your perfect tree match!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
