DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>===========</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, th
 is event is <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider our final Sa
 lem 'Tree Care' event of the season on Sat\, May 7th!</p><p>===========</p>
 <p>Help needed to plant trees at this community park in NE Salem! Back in F
 ebruary 2021 the community lost many trees due to a once-in-a-century ice s
 torm followed by the late June heat dome. Let's replant and regrow the loca
 l urban canopy! This is an under-developed park that the City of Salem is t
 ransforming into a community treasure with more trees\, a picnic shelter\, 
 playground\, soccer fields and basketball courts. Sign-up to be a part of t
 his park transformation!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be as
 signed a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, 
 tools\, and guidance. Dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you d
 on't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?<
 /b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardi
 an.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to h
 and us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth wa
 iver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What abou
 t Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one 
 priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our event
 s are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, su
 ch as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, e
 tc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductio
 ns\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\
 , bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will ne
 ed\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks o
 f this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;f
 or more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&
 nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftr
 ees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is a
 lso happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nb
 sp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftre
 es.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><
 hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Salem.</p><i>Friend
 s of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by t
 he CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe 
 to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-
 registered.</i></html-blob>
