DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>====</b></p><p><b>
 <u>Due to popular interest\, this planting is full and closed</u>.&nbsp\; <
 /b>Please consider our next NE Portland neighborhood event on Sat Dec 10th 
 (or any other open event this Fall).&nbsp\; Thank you for your interest!</p
 ><p><b>====</b></p><br><p><b>Let's plant trees in the Cully neighborhood of
  NE Portland!&nbsp\;</b>Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href
 ="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></u></b> to purchase a tr
 ee for your household or business. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will 
 be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this
  community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and 
 be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide glov
 es\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/te
 a/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear st
 urdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</
 p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young tree
 s to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. 
 Please sign up at <b><u><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.f
 riendsoftrees.org/truck</a></u></b> if you're able to help us out in this k
 ey role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 
 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can v
 olunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http:
 //friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b>&nbsp\;signe
 d by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will t
 ravel from the meeting location to several planting sites in the nearby nei
 ghborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We recommend private transportati
 on</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if o
 thers in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. Please no
 te: FOT is requiring that anyone carpooling with others outside of their ho
 usehold wear a face mask\, and crack the windows of the vehicle.&nbsp\; </p
 ><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> that all people at our ev
 ents cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to someone who t
 ested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; We <u>recomm
 end&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask whe
 n working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical distance. Please s
 ee our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volu
 nteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details
 .&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</
 b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happ
 y to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href=
 "mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u><
 /b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This 
 planting is part of an effort to remedy toxic air pollution from a nearby g
 lass plant that was fined by Oregon's DEQ. The trees planted at this event 
 will bring long-term human and environmental health benefits to the area. T
 his event is part of a coalition effort organized by Clean Air Canopy\; par
 tner groups include Verde\, Cully Association of Neighbors\, Cully Air Acti
 on Team\, and Friends of Trees.<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-b
 lob>\n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.com/kau-gmyg-zat\nOr dia
 l: (US) +1 443-606-2378 PIN: 636073706#\nMore phone numbers: https://tel.me
 et/kau-gmyg-zat?pin=5905498538471&hs=7\n\nLearn more about Meet at: https:/
 /support.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
