DESCRIPTION:===============================================================
 ==<b>Due to poplar interest\, this event is now closed to further groups si
 gning-up.</b> Please consider joining one of our other planting events.  RS
 VPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may sim
 ply show up!\n=============================================================
 ====\n\nJoin us to plant trees as part of our Beaverton Arbor Day Celebrati
 on!  We'll be at Hall Creek putting the finishing touches on this large cre
 ek restoration project. This planting is in partnership with the City of Be
 averton.\n\nPlease arrive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some hot c
 offee and breakfast treats. Look for Friends of Trees directional signs to 
 guide you to the site. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide g
 loves and tools\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather 
 and wearing sturdy\, <b>closed-toe shoes</b> (for your safety\, no sandals 
 of any kind\, please!).\n\n\nPlease contact our Volunteer & Outreach Team a
 t (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We loo
 k forward to seeing you out there!\n\nWe look forward to seeing you out the
 re!\n\n\n<b>Special thanks to Portland General Electric\, Rigert Shade Tree
 s\, and Whole Foods Market for generously sponsoring this event.</b>
