DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b>Due to popular community support\, this e
 vent is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any of our open events 
 - we hope to work with you soon!</p><p>=========</p><p><span>Let's plant tr
 ees together in East Portland! Interested in receiving a tree? Click </span
 ><b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u>
 <u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b><span> to purchase a tree f
 or your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees as well as several hu
 ndred small native trees and shrubs will be ready for planting in their new
  homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!</spa
 n></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew
 . The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\,
  as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask tha
 t all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't 
 mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><s
 pan> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  
 Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a </
 span><b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank">
 <u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b><span> sign
 ed by their parent/guardian.</span></p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: Mo
 st planting crews will travel from the meeting location to a few planting s
 ites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend priv
 ate transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to ca
 rpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.
 </p><p><b>Transit:</b> Bus<span> Line 87 with a .2 mile walk.</span></p><p>
 <b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer
  FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is 
 also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volu
 nteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><b><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></b></u></a>\, 503
 -595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank yo
 u to our event sponsors <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_bla
 nk"><u>Portland General Electric</u></a> &amp\; <a href="https://wyldcanna.
 com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>WYLD</u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event made possible t
 hrough a grant from the USDA Forest Service. This institution is an equal o
 pportunity provider.</p>
