DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><p>==========</p><p><b>Due to popular interes
 t this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any other open 
 event -- we hope to work with you soon!</p><p>==========</p><p>Let's plant 
 trees together in Beaverton! Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be rea
 dy for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this commu
 nity planting possible!<br></p><p><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in an
 d be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gl
 oves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weath
 er\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to
  have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and un
 der volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunte
 er on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their p
 arent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volun
 teers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requ
 iring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exceptio
 n of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nb
 sp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face 
 mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from 
 others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any oth
 er snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your househo
 ld feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a hre
 f="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked
  Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &
 nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbs
 p\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ web
 page</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach
  Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftr
 ees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to p
 lanting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor: Int
 ernational Paper Company<br>===&nbsp\;<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is i
 n partnership with the City of Beaverton -- thank you for your longstanding
  commitment to community tree-planting!</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to
  follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Healt
 h Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we wil
 l cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u><
 br><u></u><i><br></i><u></u><br><u></u>===<br>Thank you to our event sponso
 rs&nbsp\;<a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/">PGE</a>&nbsp\;&amp\; <a hre
 f="http://www.tree-source.net/">Rigert Shade Trees</a>!<br>===<i><br></i><u
 ></u></html-blob>
