DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><p>=========</p><p><b>Due to popular i
 nterest\, this event is <u>full and closed</u> to planting volunteers</b> (
 we are still looking for a few truck drivers\, please sign-up below).&nbsp\
 ; Thank you for your interest --&nbsp\; hope to plant with you at another e
 vent before the end of planting season in April!</p><p>=========</p><p>Let'
 s plant trees together in NE Vancouver! Interested in receiving a tree? Cli
 ck <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purc
 hase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be 
 ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this co
 mmunity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be 
 assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, 
 wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have
  fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these you
 ng trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging
  site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">w
 ww.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in
  this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that yo
 uth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and olde
 r can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;sign
 ed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will 
 travel from the meeting location to several planting sites in the nearby ne
 ighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private tran
 sportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provi
 de carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your participation\, please 
 let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of voluntee
 rs and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiri
 ng that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception o
 f those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\
 ;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mas
 k through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from oth
 ers not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other 
 snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household 
 feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Qu
 estions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbs
 p\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the fol
 lowing neighborhoods: Airport Green\, Burton Evergreen\, Burnt Bridge Creek
 \, Cimarron\, Countryside Woods\, Fircrest\, First Place\, Hearthwood\, Ima
 ge\, Landover Sharmel\, North Hearthwood\, North Image\, Parkside\, and Par
 kway East.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nb
 sp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ we
 bpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reac
 h Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoft
 rees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to 
 planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with 
 the City of Vancouver Urban Forestry – thank you for your longstanding comm
 itment to planting trees!</p><p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the
  guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Washington Department o
 f Health &amp\; Human Services. If at any point we feel it is not safe to h
 ost events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-regi
 stered.</i></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors&nbsp\;<a href="htt
 ps://mwlpdx.com/" id="ow3546" __is_owner="true"><u><u>Multnomah Whiskey Lib
 rary</u></u></a>!<br>===<i><br></i></p><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
