DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Let's plant trees together in Central Vancouver! 
 Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens o
 f large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, 
 and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please
  arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting 
 starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all
  volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind 
 getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun! </p><p><b>How do I register? </b>
 Online registration is closed at this time but there is still room availabl
 e at this event!&nbsp\; Please simply show up and sign-in at the registrati
 on table.&nbsp\;Please note that we need to split larger groups up into 3-5
  people per planting crew.<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your 
 help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away fr
 om the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.frien
 dsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're 
 able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nb
 sp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nb
 sp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us
  a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver f
 orm</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transpo
 rtation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several planting 
 sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly 
 recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be 
 unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your p
 articipation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;
 The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of
  Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated
  (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger
  than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bri
 ng and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or mor
 e of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your own water
  bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if any
 one in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please s
 ee our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunte
 er Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\
 ; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted
 ?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborhoods: Bagley Downs\, Burton Ridge\, D
 ubois Park\, Edgewood Park\, Ellsworth Springs\, Evergreen Highlands\, Fore
 st Ridge\, Father Blanchet\, Harney Heights\, Maplewood\, Marrion\, Meadow 
 Homes\, North Garrison Heights\, Northcrest\, Northwood\, Oakbrook\, Ogden\
 , Old Evergreen Highway\, South Cliff\, Vancouver Heights\, and Vanmall.<br
