DESCRIPTION:==========<br><br><b>This training is now <u>full and closed</u
 ></b> - thank you for your interest!&nbsp\; We'll update our online calenda
 r in late summer '21 with our Fall planting events and any other volunteer 
 opportunities.<br><br><br>==========<br>Summer Inspectors learn how to prop
 erly assess the health of newly-planted street and yard trees. The total ti
 me commitment is about 12 hours over four months\, including this required 
 3.5 hour online training.&nbsp\; Tree inspection routes are available in Wa
 shington (Vancouver) and Oregon (Gresham\; Portland: N\, NE\, SE\, E\; Milw
 aukie\, Oregon City\, and Wilsonville).<br><br>Any questions? Please don't 
 hesitate to be in touch with Carey\, Pablo\, or Jenny in our Volunteer &amp
 \; Outreach Program: Volunteer@Frien<u></u><u></u>dsofTrees.org .&nbsp\; We
  hope to work with you soon!
