DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this even
 t is <u>full and closed</u>. </b> Please consider our next Vancouver planti
 ng on Sat March 23rd!</p><p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees toge
 ther in Westside Vancouver! </b>Interested in receiving a tree? Click <a hr
 ef="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u>
 </u></u></a> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' 
 tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help i
 s what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45a
 m to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am
 . We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast sna
 cks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the 
 weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be rea
 dy to have fun!</p><p><b>Want to plant by bike?</b><span> This event will h
 ave a </span><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunt
 eer/bike-planter/"><u><u><u>bike-powered crew</u></u></u></a></b><span>. Br
 ing your bike\, helmet\, and a bike trailer (if you have one). Online regis
 tration has closed at this time\, please simply sign-in when you arrive!</s
 pan><br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volu
 nteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their ow
 n and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver
 "><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></a> signed by their 
 parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from 
 the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up
  to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or veh
 icle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small plant
 ing crew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees b
 e planted? </b>In the following neighborhoods: <span>Arnada\, </span><span>
 Carter Park\, </span><span>Esther Short\, Fruit Valley\, </span><span>Hough
 \, </span><span>Lincoln\, </span><span>Northwest\, Rose Village\, and </spa
 n><span>Shumway.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a hr
 ef="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer 
 FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!
   Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b>
 <u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward
  to planting together soon!<br></p><p><br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our ev
 ent sponsors <a href="https://www.exquisitecrystals.com/?gad_source=1&gclid
 =Cj0KCQiAgqGrBhDtARIsAM5s0_lXEWs3PskESrETat5Wn2DpqoqFqiK0fkWRVvglWOOhDeX506
 HA7oQaApJYEALw_wcB"><u><u><u><u>Exquisite Crystals</u></u></u></u></a> &amp
 \; <a href="https://laughingplanet.com/">Laughing Planet</a>.</p><p>===</p>
 <p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Vancou
 ver.</p>
