DESCRIPTION:<b>UPDATE: Due to weather and freezing site conditions forecast
 ed through the weekend\, this planting is postponed until further notice. W
 e apologize for any inconvenience and thank you for your flexibility!</b> I
 f you have questions please contact us at volunteer@friendsoftrees.org.\n\n
 Canceling an event is a bummer. The good news is we have several planting e
 vents next weekend on Saturday\, January 21st. Feel free to take a look at 
 those events and let us know if you'd like to attend!\n\n==\n\nPlease arriv
 e to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some hot coffee and breakfast trea
 ts.  The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves and tools\, 
 so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy
  shoes.  Our neighborhood volunteers will also provide a potluck lunch for 
 all volunteers after the planting is complete!\n\n*We're be planting in the
  neighborhoods of Bagley Downs\, Burton Ridge\, Ellsworth Springs\, Evergre
 en Highlands\, Father Blanchet Park\, Dubois Park\, Forest Ridge\, Marrion\
 , Meadow Homes\, Northcrest\, Northwood\, North Garrison Heights\, Oakbrook
 \, Ogden\, South Cliff\, Vancouver Heights\, and VanMall.\n\nPlease contact
  Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have questions or need any further 
 information.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you out there!
