DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Let's plant trees together in Oregon City!</b> Interested
  in receiving a tree? Click <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/
 "><u><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> to purchase a tree for
  your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for plant
 ing in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community plantin
 g possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a plan
 ting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and g
 uidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. W
 e ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots y
 ou don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I r
 egister? </b>Onlin<wbr /><u></u>e registration has closed at this time\, bu
 t there is still room at this event\, please simply show up at 8:45am and s
 ign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help
  getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from t
 he central staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_2
 6=a0T5G00000fQk9W&tfa_2189=Oregon%20City%20%2D%20South%20neighborhood%20pla
 nting&tfa_31=a0V5G00000W2cjW&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20April%206\,%
 202024%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-04-06&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20F
 OT&tfa_51=offsite"><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></a></b> if yo
 u're able to help out in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We req
 uest that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 an
 d older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http
 ://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u><
 /b></u></u></u></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private t
 ransportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few plant
 ing sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend
  private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option 
 to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with 
 this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the following nei
 ghborhoods: <span>Caufield\, </span><span>Gaffney Lane\, </span><span>Hazel
  Grove/Westling Farm\, </span><span>Hillendale\, South End and Tower Vista.
 </span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://frie
 ndsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u><
 /b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach 
 Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u
 ><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look for
 ward to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor
  <a href="https://wyldcanna.com/"><u>WYLD</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p></p><hr 
 /><p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Oregon City.</p>
