X-GOOGLE-CONFERENCE:https://meet.google.com/uaj-tcjg-txn
CREATED:20220829T175306Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u>
 full and closed</u>.</b> Please consider any of other open event -- we hope
  to work with you soon!</p><p><b>-------------------------------</b></p><p>
 <b>Let's plant trees together in North Portland neighborhoods of Piedmont\,
  Kenton\, and Portsmouth! </b><span> These trees will be ready for planting
  in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting p
 ossible!  </span><span>Note: this will be a relatively small planting by ou
 r standards -- if you'd like to join a more intimate community planting thi
 s is a good one!</span><br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be
  assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves
 \, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/
 hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear stur
 dy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p>
 <p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees 
 to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Pl
 ease sign up at <b><u><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.fri
 endsoftrees.org/truck</a></u></b> if you're able to help out in this key ro
 le. </p><p><b>Ride your bike?</b> There will be a bike-powered planting cre
 w at this event! Learn more and sign-up for the bike crew: <a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/bike"><u><u><u>https://friendsoftrees.org/bike</u></u><
 /u></a></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volun
 teer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own
  and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p
 ><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location t
 o several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). 
 <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there ma
 y be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also co
 mfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone carpooling w
 ith others outside of their household wear a face mask\, and crack the wind
 ows of the vehicle.  </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> Friends of Trees <u
 >requires</u> that all people at our events cancel if you feel unwell or ha
 ve been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days o
 f the event.  For safety recommendations and more visit <b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions
  webpage</a></u></b>.        </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our
  <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ we
 bpage</a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabrie
 l and Jenny at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b> We look forward to planting together soon!
 </p><p>=========</p><p>This planting is part of an effort to help ensure eq
 uitable access to clean air and a healthy environment for North Portland co
 mmunity members. When a North Portland roofing company reached a settlement
  with Oregon DEQ related to compliance with their air quality permit\, a po
 rtion of the penalty included contributing funds to approved local environm
 ental projects\, such as planting trees. The trees planted at this communit
 y event will bring long-term human and environmental health benefits to the
  area\, critical to our environmental justice efforts.<br></p><u></u><u></u
 >\n\nJoin with Google Meet: https://meet.google.com/uaj-tcjg-txn\nOr dial: 
 (US) +1 347-894-2419 PIN: 850509982#\nMore phone numbers: https://tel.meet/
 uaj-tcjg-txn?pin=9693302284000&hs=7\n\nLearn more about Meet at: https://su
 pport.google.com/a/users/answer/9282720
