DESCRIPTION:Join us in planting trees as a volunteer -- or click <a href= h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/plant-it-programs>HERE</a> to purchase a tree for
  your home.  We are planting in all NE Vancouver neighborhoods\, including:
  Airport Green\, Burnt Bridge Creek\, Countryside Woods\, Image\, North Ima
 ge\, Landover Sharmel\, First Place.\n\nPlease arrive to the staging site b
 y 8:45am to enjoy some hot coffee and breakfast treats.  The planting start
 s promptly at 9:00am. All volunteers should meet at the park entrance off o
 f NE 138th Ave. We provide gloves and tools\, so all you need to do is show
  up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy <b>closed-toe shoes</b> (for
  your safety\, no sandals of any kind\, please!).  Our neighborhood volunte
 ers will also provide a potluck lunch for all volunteers after the planting
  is complete!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly r
 equested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoft
 rees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not r
 equired for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\
 n\nPlease contact Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have questions or 
 need any further information.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you out there!\n
 \n<b>Special thanks to J. Frank Schmidt & Son Co. for generously sponsoring
  this event.</b>
