 l and closed</u></b>. Please consider signing up for another event where mo
 re volunteers are needed - thank you!</p><p>=====</p><p>Let's plant trees t
 ogether in Gresham! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</
 u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozen
 s of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes
 \, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Plea
 se arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plantin
 g starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as l
 ight breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunte
 ers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting 
 dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need
  your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks a
 way from the central staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/484
 0511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000qajaP&tfa_2189=Gresham%20neighborhood%20planting\,%20
 Gresham&tfa_31=a0VPa000008zJZ8&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20November%2
 022\,%202025%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2025-11-22&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standa
 rd%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sig
 n up</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help in this
  key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under v
 olunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their
  own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/yo
 uthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u>
 </u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transpor
 tation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sit
 es in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend privat
 e transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carp
 ool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. <
 /p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ w
 ebpage</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist! 
  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.o
 rg" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u>
 </u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p>
 <p><b>What neighborhoods will the trees be planted in?</b> Parts of Rockwoo
 d\, Centennial\, Northeast\, Northwest\, Wilkes East\, North Gresham\, and 
