DESCRIPTION:<br><i><br></i>Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are cruc
 ial to planting trees properly and leading groups of volunteers from the pu
 blic at more than 25 planting events (5 in Vancouver and Clark County) this
  coming planting season. Friends of Trees is aiming to plant more than 3\,0
 00 street and yard trees in our Neighborhood Trees Program\, and we can't d
 o it without your help!<br><br>We have another Crew Leader training in SE P
 ortland on November 2nd if that works better for your schedule. Curriculum 
 for each training is the same and once completed\, you will be able to volu
 nteer at Neighborhood Trees events throughout Portland\, Vancouver\, Beaver
 ton\, Gresham\, Oregon City\, and Wilsonville!<br><br>The training is free 
 (and includes breakfast snacks\, lunch\, and a t-shirt!) but registration i
 s required. <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/crew-leader-training/">R
 egister HERE</a></b> to save your spot\, space limited.<br><br>Please conta
 ct Jenny or Pablo if you need more information: 503-595-0213 // <a href="ma
 ilto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>. We loo
 k forward to answering any questions you may have!<br><br>===<br>Thank you 
 to our sponsor <a href="http://www.tree-source.net/">Rigert Shade Trees</a>
 !<br>===&nbsp\;
