CREATED:20210819T225812Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Let's plant trees together in Central NE Portland
 ! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.
 org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens
  of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\
 , and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Plea
 se arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plantin
 g starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that a
 ll volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't min
 d getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun! </p><p><b>How do I register? </
 b>Online pre-registration for this event is now closed but we still have sp
 ace available for about 30 more planting volunteers! Simply show up to the 
 address above by 8:40am to register and be assigned a crew.<br><br><b>Have 
 a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their pl
 anting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign u
 p at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u
 >ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp
 \;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under vol
 unteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on t
 heir own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/g
 uardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meet
 ing location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to se
 veral miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\
 ;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling option
 s. If this is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><
 b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our 
 number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people a
 t our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are inel
 igible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocomp
 romised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event 
 introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own
  household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages 
 you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within 
 two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b><
 /a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>
 Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborhoods
 : Madison South\, Rose City Park\, Sumner\, Beaumont-Wilshire\, Cully\, Ros
 eway\, and Hollywood.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check
  out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volun
 teer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; Y
 ou can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer
 @friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look 
 forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in pa
 rtnership with the City of Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – th
 ank you for your longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><i>Friends o
 f Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the 
 CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to 
 host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-reg
 istered.</i></html-blob>
