DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=====</b></p><p><b>Due to popular community support\, thi
 s event is <u>full and closed</u>. </b>Please consider any other event - we
  hope to work with you soon!</p><p><b>=====</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees 
 together in NE Vancouver!</b><span> Interested in receiving a tree? Click <
 /span><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>HE
 RE</u></b></u></u></u></u></a><span> to purchase a tree for your household.
  Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new
  homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!</spa
 n><br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting 
 crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidan
 ce\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask
  that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you do
 n't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup t
 ruck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sit
 es a few blocks away from the central staging site.<a href="https://www.tfa
 forms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000fQk9V&tfa_2189=NE%20Vancouver%20neighbor
 hood%20planting&tfa_31=a0V5G00000W2cjS&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20Ma
 rch%2023\,%202024%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-03-23&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=S
 tandard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite"> <b><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u
 ></b></a> if you're able to help out in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age
  18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardia
 n.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us 
 a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth w
 aiver form</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p>
 <p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location
  to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). 
 <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there ma
 y be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also co
 mfortable with this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In th
 e following neighborhoods: <span>Airport Green\, </span><span>Burnt Bridge 
 Creek\, </span><span>Burton Evergreen\, </span><span>Cimarron\, </span><spa
 n>Countryside Woods\, </span><span>Fircrest\, </span><span>First Place\, </
 span><span>Hearthwood\, </span><span>Image\, </span><span>Kevanna Park\, </
 span><span>Landover-Sharmel\, </span><span>North Hearthwood\, </span><span>
 North Image\, </span><span>Parkside\, and </span><span>Parkway East.</span>
 </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftr
 ees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u>
 </u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel
  and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b>
 <u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward
  to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a 
 href="https://laughingplanet.com/"><u>Laughing Planet</u></a>.</p><p>===</p
 ><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Vanco
 uver.</p>
