DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>Let's plant trees together in
  the North Lancaster &amp\; East Lancaster neighborhoods of NE Salem! </b>D
 ozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new h
 omes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>
 Please arrive by 8:45am at the McKay City Park - East parking lot to sign-i
 n and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provid
 e gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and cof
 fee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, w
 ear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have 
 fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this
  time\, but there is still room at this event.  Please simply show-up and s
 ign-in when you arrive!<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 1
 5 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volun
 teer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendso
 ftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b> signed by their paren
 t/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the m
 eeting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to
  a mile). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, bu
 t there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew a
 re also comfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone ca
 rpooling with others outside of their household wear a face mask\, and crac
 k the windows of the vehicle.  </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>req
 uire</u> that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or 
 have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days
  of the event.  We <u>recommend </u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring an
 d wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physi
 cal distance. Please see our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</a></u></b> for mo
 re details.        </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a 
 href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a><
 /u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel and Jenn
 y at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org</a></u></b> We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr
  /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Salem.<br></p><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
