DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><p><b>=========</b></p><p><b>This event is <u>full and closed</u>.&n
 bsp\;</b> Thank you for your interest -- please consider any open future ev
 ents!</p><p><b>=========</b></p><p><b>Join the fun at <u>Plant-a-palooza!</
 u></b><b> at Level Beer</b><span>\,&nbsp\;</span><span>a Clean Air Canopy e
 vent focused on planting in the Argay and Wilkes neighborhoods.</span><br><
 /p><p>Interested in receiving a free tree(s) for your household? Click&nbsp
 \;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u>HERE</u></a></u
 ></b>&nbsp\;to see your options!&nbsp\;</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am at Le
 vel Beer to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at
  9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakf
 ast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress f
 or the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and
  be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b>&nbsp\;We need your
  help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away f
 rom the central staging site. Please sign up at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http:/
 /www.friendsoftrees.org/truck"><u>www.friendsoftrees.org/truck</u></a></u><
 /b>&nbsp\;if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>
 Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a
  parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and 
 will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youth
 waiver"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/g
 uardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meet
 ing location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to se
 veral miles).&nbsp\;<b>We recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike 
 or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small
  planting crew are also comfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requirin
 g that anyone carpooling with others outside of their household wear a face
  mask\, and crack the windows of the vehicle.&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Event safety:
 </b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require</u>&nbsp\;that all people at our events canc
 el if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to someone who tested pos
 itive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>rec
 ommend</u>&nbsp\;everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask 
 when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical distance. Pleas
 e see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><
 u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for mo
 re details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\
 ;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our 
 team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbs
 p\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u>volunteer@friends
 oftrees.org</u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon
 !</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://portla
 ndgeneral.com/"><u><u>PGE</u></u></a>.<br>===</p><b><hr></b><p>The trees pl
 anted at this event will bring long-term human and environmental health ben
 efits to the area. This event is part of a coalition effort organized by Cl
 ean Air Canopy\; partner groups include Verde\, Cully Association of Neighb
 ors\, Cully Air Action Team\, and Friends of Trees.</p><u></u><u></u><u></u
 ><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
