DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Wilsonville! Interested in rec
 eiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HE
 RE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' ta
 ll) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is 
 what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am
  to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am.
  We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress
  for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, a
 nd be ready to have fun! </p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registrati
 on has closed for this event\, but you're welcome to simply show up!&nbsp\;
  We'll ask you to sign-in when you arrive.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp
 \;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp
 \; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a
 &nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver for
 m</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transport
 ation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several planting si
 tes in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly re
 commend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be un
 likely able to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your par
 ticipation\, please let us know.<br></p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp
 \;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends 
 of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinat
 ed (with the exception of those younger than 12and anyone&nbsp\;severely im
 munocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and 
 wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of di
 stance from others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle
  and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in 
 your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&
 nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Freq
 uently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.</p><p>Please
  contact Jenny and Carey at <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">v
 olunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any fu
 rther information. We look forward to seeing you out there!</p><b><hr></b><
 p>This event is in partnership with the City of Wilsonville.</p><i>Friends 
 of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the
  CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to
  host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-re
 gistered.</i>
