DESCRIPTION:<p>======</p><p><b>This event is now full and closed</b>. Pleas
 e consider our second training option next week\, on Wed Sept 24th. Each se
 ssion is the same and will prepare you to be a Canopy Caller with FOT this 
 planting season!</p><p>======</p><p>Would you like to help get more trees p
 lanted in the greater-Portland/Vancouver metro area while talking with peop
 le interested in the same thing? Do you like learning about trees?  Are you
  open to connecting with people on the phone?  If so\, we have a volunteer 
 role for you -- the <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to
 -volunteer/canopy-caller/" target="_blank">Canopy Caller</a></b>!  </p><p>C
 anopy Callers connect with interested neighbors on the phone to help them f
 ind the right tree for their space and tastes\, as well as let them know ho
 w they can volunteer at the planting event in their neighborhood. It’s a bi
 t of community organizing and a bit of customer service—all with the missio
 n of increasing our urban canopy!</p><p><b>"I'm interested! How do I sign-u
 p?"</b> This session is closed.  Please consider the next training option o
 n Wed\, 9/24: <b><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe5GrXmA
 J-lMhQs9wH77BoePLb-K6HlHHYzBMgrz-McPnzdgA/viewform" target="_blank">Registe
 r here</a></b>.  Space limited.</p><p>Following the training\, we ask that 
 you commit to four (or more!) call nights (this role takes some time and pr
 actice to master).  You can join call nights at the office or remotely (if 
 you’re willing to set up Google Voice for free on your cell phone).  There 
 are 2-3 call nights each month to choose from\, Sept-Feb. </p><p>Questions?
  Please connect with Cece and Jenny: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftre
 es.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213.</p
 >
