DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><p><span><u></u>===========<u></u><br>
 <u></u><br><u></u><br><b>Thanks to community support\, this event is now <u
 >full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any of our other open events -- w
 e have a very high need for tree planters in Oregon City on April 2nd!&nbsp
 \;</span></p><p><span>&nbsp\;</span></p><p><span>Thank you for your interes
 t--we hope to see you soon!<br><u></u><br><u></u><br>===========</span>&nbs
 p\;</p><p>Let's plant trees together in West Gresham! Interested in receivi
 ng a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</
 a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) 
 trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what
  makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to 
 sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We 
 provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress for
  the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and b
 e ready to have fun!<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help g
 etting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the
  central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftr
 ees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able t
 o help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We
  request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Y
 outh 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbs
 p\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a
 ></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportatio
 n</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several planting sites 
 in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recomm
 end private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlike
 ly able to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrier to your partici
 pation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The sa
 fety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees
 . We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with
  the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 
 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and
  wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of d
 istance from others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottl
 e and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in
  your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our
 &nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Fre
 quently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbs
 p\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp
 \;</b>In the following neighborhoods: Rockwood\, Wilkes East\, North Gresha
 m\, and Centennial.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check o
 ut our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunte
 er FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You
  can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@f
 riendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look fo
 rward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in part
 nership with the City of Gresham.</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follo
 w the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Auth
 ority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will canc
 el them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u><br><u>
 </u><i><br></i><u></u><br><u></u><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors
 &nbsp\;<a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/">Portland General Electric</a>
 &nbsp\;&amp\; <a href="https://www.providence.org/">Providence</a>!<br>===<
 i><br></i><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
