CREATED:20230829T132922Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><span><b>=====</b></span></p><p><b>Due to popular community 
 support\, this event is <u>full and closed</u>. </b>Please consider any oth
 er open event - we hope to work with you soon!</p><p><b>=====</b></p><p><b>
 Volunteers needed for climate action! </b><span>On March 16th\, Friends of 
 Trees and Multnomah County are hosting a tree planting event in East Multno
 mah County neighborhoods. </span><b><u>The 72 trees planted at this event w
 ill serve as a memorial to the 72 lives lost in Multnomah County from heat-
 related illness during summer 2021</u></b><span>. Community support needed 
 to help plant the trees that will shade these low-canopy neighborhoods. </s
 pan><br></p><p><span>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a p
 lanting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, an
 d guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate
 . We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boot
 s you don't mind getting dirty\, and be make a difference for shade equity!
 </span></p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b><span> We need your help getting t
 hese young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central
  staging site. </span><b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a
 0T5G00000fQk9S&tfa_2189=Gresham/East%20Portland%20memorial%20planting&tfa_3
 1=a0V5G00000W2cjG&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20March%2016\,%202024%20a
 t%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-03-16&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=
 offsite"><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></a></b><span> if you're
  able to help out in this key role. </span><br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> 
 We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth
  16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href
 ="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver 
 form</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p
 ><b>Private transportation</b><span>: You will travel from the meeting loca
 tion to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several mile
 s). </span><b>We recommend private transportation</b><span> (bike or vehicl
 e)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting
  crew are also comfortable with this. </span><br></p><p><b>Where will these
  trees be planted? </b>In the following neighborhoods:  Centennial\, Glenfa
 ir\, Hazelwood\, Mill Park\, and Rockwood.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please 
 check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u>
 <u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our tea
 m is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto
 :Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftree
 s.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together 
 soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://portland
 general.com/"><u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===
 </p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This event is held in partnership with Multnomah
  County. <br></p>
