DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>Let's plant trees 
 together in the South Beaverton neighborhood!</b>&nbsp\;Forty&nbsp\;large (
 6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes at this eve
 nt\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>P
 lease arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plan
 ting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well a
 s light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volu
 nteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getti
 ng dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register?&nbsp\;</b>
 <span> Pre-registration is closed\, but your help is still needed! Simply s
 how up on Saturday to sign a waiver and be assigned a crew!</span><br><br><
 b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with
  a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own an
 d will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/you
 thwaiver"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent
 /guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require</u>&
 nbsp\;that people cancel their participation if you are feeling unwell or h
 ave been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days 
