DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>This event is now <u>full and closed
 </u>. </b> Please consider any of the other available planting events.  Tha
 nk you!</p><p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees together in North P
 ortland!</b><span> Interested in receiving a tree? Click </span><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></a><
 span> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) t
 rees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what 
 makes this community planting possible!</span><br></p><p>Please arrive by 8
 :45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:
 00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast
  snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for 
 the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be
  ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help get
 ting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the c
 entral staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0
 T5G00000fQk9F&tfa_2189=North%20Portland%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0
 V5G00000W2ciX&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20December%209\,%202023%20at%
 208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2023-12-09&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=of
 fsite"><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></a></b> if you're able to help out in t
 his key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and und
 er volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on t
 heir own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/yout
 hwaiver"><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></a> signed by their 
 parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from 
 the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up
  to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or veh
 icle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small plant
 ing crew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees b
 e planted? </b>In the neighborhoods of <span>Portsmouth and St. Johns.</spa
 n></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></
 u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href
 ="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together
  soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br></p>
