DESCRIPTION:<p>========</p><p><b>Due to generous community support\, this e
 vent is <u>full and closed</u>.</b> <i>We are still looking for truck drive
 rs if you have access to a pick-up truck without a canopy (see more details
  below.</i></p><p>========</p><p>Let's plant trees together in Westside Van
 couver!  Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to pur
 chase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be
  ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this c
 ommunity planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be
  assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves
 \, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/
 hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear stur
 dy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p>
 <p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We're fortunate to be full for truck drivers
  for this event. Please consider the next Vancouver planting on Sat\, March
  28th in NE neighborhoods!</p><p><b>Want to plant by bike?</b> Fill out <b>
 <a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000qajab&tfa_2189=W
 estside%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting\,%20Vancouver&tfa_31=a0VPa000
 0096tB7&tfa_45=%20at%20February%2028\,%202026%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_2190=202
 6-02-28&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank">
 <u><u>this quick registration form</u></u></a></b>.  Bring your helmet and 
 a bike trailer you're willing to move trees in\, if you have one!</p><p><b>
 Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a paren
 t/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to
  hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardia
 n.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting lo
 cation to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several mi
 les). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but th
 ere may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are a
 lso comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check ou
 t our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist
 ! <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u><
 /b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look 
 forward to working together soon!<br></p><p><b>What neighborhoods will the 
 trees be planted in?</b> Arnada\, Carter Park\, Esther Short\, Fruit Valley
 \, Hough\, Lincoln\, Northwest\, and Shumway.</p><b><hr /></b><p></p><p>Thi
 s event in partnership with City of Vancouver.</p>
