DESCRIPTION:Summer Inspectors learn how to assess the health of newly-plant
 ed street and yard trees and give homeowners watering and mulching tips.  B
 eing a Summer Inspector gives you a chance to meet your neighbors and help 
 them take care of their trees during the critical first summer after planti
 ng.\n\nYou can register for this training here: www.friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer/trainings/summer-inspector-training\n\nPlease contact Andy Meeks at A
 ndyM@FriendsofTrees.org\, or call 503-595-0213 for more information or to s
 ign up for this very popular volunteer role. Spaces will be limited!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:St. Paul's Lutheran Church\, 3880 SE Brooklyn Street Portland OR
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Summer Inspector Training
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
