CREATED:20250820T225853Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <
 u>full and closed</u>.</b>  We hope to work with you at another event!</p><
 p>=========</p><p>Let's plant trees together in Beaverton!  Interested in r
 eceiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree
 /" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>HE
 RE</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' t
 all) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is
  what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am
  to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am.
  We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snac
 ks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the w
 eather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be read
 y to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting 
 these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the centra
 l staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00
 000qajah&tfa_2189=Beaverton%20neighborhood%20planting\,%20Beaverton&tfa_31=
 a0VPa000008zJaJ&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20April%204\,%202026%20at%2
 08:30%20am&tfa_2190=2026-04-04&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=off
 site" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to help in this ke
 y role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volu
 nteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their ow
 n and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youth
 waiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Pri
 vate transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few
  planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We rec
 ommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an o
 ption to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable
  with this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mail
 to:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look forward to work
 ing together soon!<br></p><b><hr /></b><p></p><p>This event in partnership 
 with City of Beaverton.</p>
