UID:7dpo92dlf1ad0mhctb4n9cpnfb@google.com
CREATED:20210819T232215Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b>Due to popular support this event is now 
 <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider signing-up for any of ou
 r open plantings!&nbsp\; The next planting in Oregon City will be Sat\, Apr
 il 2nd!</p><p>=========</p><p>Let's plant trees together in Oregon City! In
 terested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/
 get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of 
 large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, an
 d your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please ar
 rive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting sta
 rts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all vo
 lunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind get
 ting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We
  need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few blo
 cks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http:
 //www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b>
  if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age
  18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/g
 uardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need
  to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">you
 th waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Priv
 ate transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to severa
 l planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b
 >We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, a
 nd will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this is a barrie
 r to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?
 </b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at
  Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully
 -vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 12 and anyone&nbsp\;s
 everely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;
 bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or 
 more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your own wa
 ter bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if 
 anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Pleas
 e see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volu
 nteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.</p
 ><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the following North Oregon
  City neighborhoods: Barclay Hills\, Canemah\, McLoughlin\, Park Place\, Ri
 vercrest\, and South End.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check
  out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volun
 teer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; Y
 ou can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer
 @friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look 
 forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partne
 rship with the City of Oregon City.</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to fol
 low the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Au
 thority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will ca
 ncel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><br><i><br><
 /i><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://getchip
 drop.com/">Chipdrop</a>!<br>===&nbsp\;<i><br></i>
