 /boots you don&#39\;t mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!  *<spa
 n>Please note: Level is an all-ages property. </span><span> </span></p><p><
 b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to t
 heir planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. <b><a 
 href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26%
 3Da0T5G00000fQk9B%26tfa_2189%3DNE%2520Portland%2520neighborhood%2520plantin
 g%26tfa_31%3Da0V5G00000W2ciH%26tfa_45%3DTruck%2520Driver\,%2520%2520at%2520
 December%252016\,%25202023%2520at%25208:30%2520am%26tfa_2190%3D2023-12-16%2
 6tfa_49%3D4.5%26tfa_886%3DStandard%2520FOT%26tfa_51%3Doffsite&amp\;sa=D&amp
 \;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1702847383189269&amp\;usg=AOvVaw363Sq627AOYAdqA6
 0lQBXo" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></a></b> if you&
 #39\;re able to help out in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We 
 request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16
  and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="h
 ttps://www.google.com/url?q=http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver&amp\;sa=D
 &amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1702847383189269&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2_0tWzy1rbqE
 1dpef6K5Wo" target="_blank"><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u
 ></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation<
 /b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in t
 he nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private trans
 portation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if 
 others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><
 b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the following neighborhoods: Ar
 gay\, Parkrose\, and Wilkes.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our 
 <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-
 faq/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1702847383189269&amp\;usg=AOvV
 aw2HHHvhm0iqjlJvzfqUagsA" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ w
 ebpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Rea
 ch us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><
 u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We l
 ook forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our ev
 ent sponsor <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://portlandgeneral.c
 om/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1702847383189269&amp\;usg=AOvVa
 w3KtGj1hMpa4EthT1FuZ6co" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Portland General Electric
 </u></u></u></a> and <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://wyldcann
 a.com/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1702847383189269&amp\;usg=AO
 vVaw0LXmwfatLxCdCVMi19gdHQ" target="_blank">WYLD</a>.</p><p>===</p><p></p><
 hr><p></p><br><p>This planting is part of Clean Air Canopy\, a coalition ef
 fort to help ensure equitable access to clean air and a healthy environment
  for Northeast Portland community members. When a NE Portland glass plant r
 eached a settlement with Oregon DEQ related to compliance with their air qu
 ality permit\, a portion of the penalty contributed funds to approved local
  environmental projects\, including planting trees. The trees planted at th
 is community event will bring long-term human and environmental health bene
 fits to the area\, critical to our environmental justice efforts. Partner g
 roups include Verde\, Cully Association of Neighbors\, Cully Air Action Tea
 m\, and Friends of Trees.</p>
