DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Let's plant trees together in SE Vancouver!</b> Intereste
 d in receiving a tree? Click <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree
 /"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a> to purchase a 
 tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready f
 or planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community
  planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigne
 d a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools
 \, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot choc
 olate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes
 /boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Ho
 w do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but ther
 e is still room at this event! Please simply sign-in when you arrive!<br><b
 r><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> This event is full for truck drivers.  Please
  consider our next Vancouver planting on Sat\, Jan 13th if you have a pick-
 up to offer!<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under
  volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on the
 ir own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></
 a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: Yo
 u will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the near
 by neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportati
 on</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others 
 in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Where
  will these trees be planted? </b>In the following neighborhoods: <span>Bel
 la Vista\, Bennington\, Cascade Highlands</span><span>\, </span><span>Casca
 de Park West\, </span><span>Cascade Southeast\, </span><span>East Mill Plai
 n\, </span><span>East Old Evergreen Hwy\, </span><span>Fairway / 164th Ave\
 , </span><span>Fishers Creek\, </span><span>Fishers Landing East\, </span><
 span>Lewis and Clark Woods\, </span><span>Mountain View\, </span><span>Nort
 hfield\, </span><span>Riveridge\, </span><span>Village at Fishers Landing\,
  and </span><span>Wildwood.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check ou
 t our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u
 >Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy
  to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><
 u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We l
 ook forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This e
 vent is in partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
