DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><br>====<br><br>Due to popular interes
 t this event is now&nbsp\;<u><b>full and closed</b></u>.&nbsp\; We hope to 
 work with you next planting/tree care season -- events start again in Oct!<
 br><br>====<p>Let's celebrate Earth Day by planting trees together in Wilso
 nville! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. 
 Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new 
 homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><b
 r>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The p
 lanting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask 
 that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don
 't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup tr
 uck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting site
 s a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a 
 href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/tr
 uck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><
 b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with
  a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own an
 d will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youth
 waiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p
 ><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting locatio
 n to planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\
 ;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\
 , and will be able to provide carpooling options due to C19 safety. If this
  is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What abo
 ut Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one
  priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our even
 ts are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 5 and any
 one&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,
 </b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, res
 pect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring 
 your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and
  cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this e
 vent. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-fa
 q/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more 
 details.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage<
 /a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabr
 iel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.o
 rg"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planti
 ng together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the Ci
 ty of Wilsonville.</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guideline
 s and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at an
 y point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and not
 ify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u><u></u></html-blob><br
 ><html-blob><i><br></i></html-blob><br><html-blob>===<br>Thank you to our e
 vent sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://2townsciderhouse.com/" id="ow4899" __is
 _owner="true"><u>2 Towns Ciderhouse</u></a>!<br>===<i><br></i></html-blob>
