DESCRIPTION:<p><b>===============</b></p><p><b>Registration is now FULL &am
 p\; CLOSED\, please consider registering for our 2/15 Cedar Hill/Cedar Mill
 s neighborhood planting event.</b></p><p><b>===============</b></p><p><br><
 /p><p>Let's plant trees together in West Beaverton! We will be planting doz
 ens of large (6-10' tall) trees at their new homes\, and your help is what 
 makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to si
 gn-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We pr
 ovide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and
  coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather
 \, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to h
 ave fun!</p><p><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under 
 volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on thei
 r own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/y
 outhwaiver" target="_blank"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></u></b> signed by 
 their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel
  from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborho
 od (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike 
 or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small
  planting crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Meeting location No
 te: </b>We will be meeting by the community garden on SW Bonnie Brae\, ther
 e were be signs pointing you to the correct location. </p><p><b>Questions? 
  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunte
 er-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reac
 h Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_
 blank"><u><b><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u
 ></b></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p
 ><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https://portlandgeneral
 .com/" target="_blank"><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></a> &amp\; <
 a href="https://www.hamptonlumber.com/" target="_blank">Hampton Lumber</a>.
 </p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the 
 City of Beaverton.</p>
