DESCRIPTION:On Oct. 25\, the City of Gresham and the Gresham Redevelopment 
 Commission in partnership with Friends of Trees and AmeriCorps will celebra
 te national Make a Difference Day by planting trees\, picking up refuse\, a
 nd removing graffiti in the Rockwood-West Gresham Urban Renewal area.\n\nTh
 e event will begin at 9 a.m. at the Rockwood Community Police Office\, 1870
 9 S.E. Stark. Gresham Mayor Shane Bemis and Police Chief Carla Piluso are e
 xpected to open the event.\n\nThe Oct. 25 event is a kick-off to future str
 eet tree plantings the City will organize with Friends of Trees. Another st
 reet tree planting will take place on March 21\, 2009 in the Centennial Eas
 t\, north Gresham\, Rockwood\, and Wilkes East neighborhoods. Event organiz
 ers hope to plant 100 trees at this second event. Residents interested in o
 rdering trees for the March 21 event should visit www.FriendsofTrees.org  f
 or more information.  Homeowners are asked to pay $20 of the $175-cost of t
 he street tree purchase\, hole digging\, planting\, mulching\, and follow-u
 p maintenance checks during the summer.\n\nThis event is sponsored by J. Fr
 ank Schmidt & Son Co.
