DESCRIPTION:Portland's mild climate allows hundreds of species of trees to 
 thrive in the city.  Can you identify them all?  Use the power of observati
 on to hone your identification skills.  Join Kris Day\, Friends of Trees Ne
 ighborhood Trees Contractor Specialist & Green Space Initiative Outreach Sp
 ecialist\, for this three hour workshop.  The workshop will begin with an i
 n-class overview of tree classification followed by a guided tour through t
 he Portsmouth neighborhood to examine leaf\, bark\, flower and stem charact
 eristics.
