CREATED:20210820T222005Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Central SE Portland! Intereste
 d in receiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-t
 ree/">HERE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (
 6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your 
 help is what makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arrive b
 y 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at
  9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all voluntee
 rs dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting d
 irty\, and be ready to have fun! </p><p><b>How do I register?&nbsp\;</b>Onl
 ine registration is closed at this time\, but this event is still open and 
 taking more planting volunteers -- please simply show up and sign-in when y
 ou arrive!<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting the
 se young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central s
 taging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/tr
 uck" id="ow804" __is_owner="true">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></
 b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>This ev
 ent will have a bike crew!</b>&nbsp\;Want to join the team planting trees b
 y bike? Sign up at&nbsp\;<b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/bike">ww
 w.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/bike</a></b>. Bikers with trailers and cargo bi
 kes are awesome but anyone with a bike is welcome to take part!&nbsp\;<b><b
 r></b></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under 
 volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer o
 n their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their paren
 t/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the m
 eeting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to
  several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nb
 sp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling opt
 ions. If this is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><
 p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is o
 ur number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all peopl
 e at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are i
 neligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunoc
 ompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the eve
 nt introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their 
 own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverag
 es you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell with
 in two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</
 b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p>
 <b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborho
 ods: Buckman\, Hosford Abernethy\, Richmond\, Montavilla\, Mt. Tabor\, Sout
 h Tabor\, Laurelhurst\, Kerns\, Sunnyside\, and North Tabor.<br></p><p><b>Q
 uestions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our
  team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and J
 enny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</
 p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Portland’s Bu
 reau of Environmental Services – thank you for your longstanding commitment
  to planting trees!</p><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guid
 elines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If 
 at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them an
 d notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><br><i><br></i><br><br>=
 ==<br>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://getchipdrop.com
 /">Chipdrop</a>&nbsp\;!<br>===&nbsp\;<i><br></i>
