DESCRIPTION:<br><b>===========</b><br><b>Thanks to popular interest\, this 
 training is <u>full and closed</u>.</b><br><b>===========</b><br><br><a hre
 f="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"><u>P
 lanting C</u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volun
 teer/crew-leader/"><u>rew Leaders</u></a> are trained volunteers who are cr
 ucial to planting trees and leading small group at our community planting e
 vents. Friends of Trees can not run these events without the support of thi
 s valued position!  After your training\, we expect you to help lead a crew
  at 4 Saturday morning events Oct-Nov (select for events that fit your sche
 dule!).    <br><br><u>This is the hands-on training for new Crew Leaders in
  Salem.  Please note: trainees will need to have completed the online train
 ing before they attend this hands-on session</u>.  The online session will 
 be available for two weeks prior for you to complete from home.<br><br>Trai
 nees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn about tree identific
 ation\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet the staff you'll b
 e working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="https://fr
