DESCRIPTION:Join us in planting trees as a volunteer -- or click <a href= h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/plant-it-programs>HERE</a> to purchase a tree for
  your home.  We're planting in the neighborhoods of Bella Vista\, Benningto
 n\, Cascade Highlands\, Cascade Southeast\, Fairway/ 164th\, Fisherâs Cre
 ek\, Fisherâs Landing East\, Lewis & Clark Woods\, Mt. View\, Northfield\
 ,  Riverridge\, Village at Fisherâs Landing\, and Wildwood.\n\nPlease arr
 ive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some hot coffee and breakfast tr
 eats.  The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves and tools\
 , so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing stur
 dy shoes.  Our neighborhood volunteers will also provide a potluck lunch fo
 r all volunteers after the planting is complete!\n\n<u><b>Calling all pick 
 up truck owners!</b></u> If you have a pick-up truck and are willing to mov
 e trees with us at this event\, <a href= http://friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 ring/how-can-you-help/drive-your-pick-up-truck-for-us>PLEASE SIGN UP HERE</
 a>. Truck driver volunteers make sure all trees arrive at their final desti
 nation on planting day and are crucial to the success of our events. Open b
 eds and trailers are encouraged!\n\n<b>This even is now full and closed to 
 further groups</b> Please consider volunteering at our next Vancouver plant
 ing on Jan 14th instead!  Alternatively\, we have a Tualatin and SE Portlan
 d planting happening at this same date/time.  RSVPs are not required for in
 dividuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may simply show up!\n\nPlease cont
 act Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more 
 information.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you out there!\n\n<b>Thank you to
  Whole Foods and the Port of Portland for generously sponsoring this planti
 ng event!<b>\n\n
