CREATED:20230830T161146Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Let's plant trees together in Northern Oregon City! </b>I
 nterested in receiving a tree? Click <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/ge
 t-a-tree/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> to purchase a
  tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready 
 for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this communit
 y planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assign
 ed a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tool
 s\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot cho
 colate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoe
 s/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>H
 ow do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but the
 re is still room at this event! Simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.
 <br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> This event is full for truck drivers --
  please consider a future neighborhood event instead. <br><br><b>Under age 
 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian
 .  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a
  <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><b><u>youth wa
 iver form</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><
 p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location 
 to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <
 b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may
  be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also com
 fortable with this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the
  following neighborhoods: Canemah\, Elyville\, McLoughlin\, Park Place\, Ri
 vercrest\, South End\, and Two Rivers. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please che
 ck out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><b>
 <u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy t
 o assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u>
 <u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></a> We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This event is i
 n partnership with the City of Oregon City.</p>
