 g: Arnada\, Carter Park\, Central Park\, Edgewood Park\, Fourth Plain Villa
 ge\, Fruit Valley\, Harney Heights\, Hough\, Hudsons Bay\,  Lincoln\, Maple
 wood\, Northwest\, Rose Village\, Shumway\, and West Minnehaha. \n\nPlease 
 arrive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some hot coffee and breakfast
  treats.  The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves and too
 ls\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing s
 turdy shoes.  Our neighborhood volunteers will also provide a potluck lunch
  for all volunteers after the planting is complete!\n\n<b>Looking to volunt
 eer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 pe
 ople - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registrat
 ion>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 
 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\n<b>This event will have people pla
 nting trees by bike! Want to join the bike team?</b> Sign up <a href=http:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/how-can-you-help/plant-trees-by-bike>HERE.
 </a> Bikers with trailers and cargo bikes are awesome and everyone with a b
 ike is welcome to take part of our bike planting efforts.\n\nPlease contact
  Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have questions or need any further 
 information.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you out there!
