DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Hillsboro! Interested in recei
 ving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" t
 arget="_blank"><u><u>HERE</u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your h
 ousehold. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in 
 their new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possi
 ble!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting cr
 ew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance
 \, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask t
 hat all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don'
 t mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register
 ? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but there is still room
  at this event! Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.<br><br><
 b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to t
 heir planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. <b><a 
 href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000IOB6w&tfa_2189=Hill
 sboro%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0VPa0000042U1i&tfa_45=Truck%20Drive
 r\,%20%20at%20December%207\,%202024%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-12-07&tf
 a_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u>Pleas
 e sign up</u></u></a></b> if you're able to help out in this key role. <br>
 <br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with 
 a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will 
 need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" tar
 get="_blank"><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></a></u></b> signed by their pa
 rent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from th
 e meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up t
 o several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehic
 le)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small plantin
 g crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please chec
 k out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target=
 "_blank"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy 
 to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@frien
 dsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></
 a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><h
 r /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Hillsboro.</p>
