DESCRIPTION:****************<br><br>Thank you for your interest!  This work
  party is now <u>full and closed</u> to further volunteer support -- please
  consider any of our other open events\, and thank you for your considerati
 on!<br><br>****************<br><br>Join the fun this Earth Month by plantin
 g large (6-12' tall) neighborhood trees in Rockwood and Wilkes East\, as we
 ll as small native trees and shrubs at Nadaka Nature Park\, which serves as
  the staging ground for this event.<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-
 in and enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The
  planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidan
 ce\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing s
 turdy shoes or boots â and be ready to have fun! <br><br><b>Have a pickup
  truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting s
 ites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b>
 <a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck" target="_blank">www.friendsof
 trees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role. <br
 ><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A signed <b><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/im
 ages/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a></b
 > is required for you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and yo
 unger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>This event is in partnership with
  Friends of Nadaka Nature Park and with support from the Nature Conservancy
  and the Boeing Company.  <br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey 
 at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="
 _blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any 
 further information. We look forward to seeing you out there!<br><br>===<br
 ><br>Thank you to our event sponsors\, <a href="https://www.portlandgeneral
 .com/" target="_blank">PGE</a>\, <a href="https://www.portofportland.com/" 
 target="_blank">Port of Portland</a>\, and <a href="https://www.jfschmidt.c
 om/" target="_blank">J. Frank Schmidt &amp\; Son Co</a>.<br><br>===&nbsp\; 
