DESCRIPTION:=============<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this workshop
  is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider joining any of our other op
 en events -- we hope to work with you soon!<br><br>=============<br><u><br>
 </u><br><u>Di<u></u>d you know that proper structural pruning when a tree i
 s young is an effective tool to help mitigate major tree failures from wind
  and ice storms</u>?  A few strategic pruning cuts can help a young tree li
 ve a long and health life in our urban environment!<p>Fri<u></u>ends of Tre
 es is offering a free young-tree structural pruning workshop.  This complet
 ely outdoors workshop will teach you how to identify pruning needs\, how an
 d when to prune trees\, how to use different tools (no chainsaws though!)\,
  and more.</p><p><b><u>What can I expect from the workshop?</u></b><span> P
 articipants will learn from and practice alongside FOT staff and experience
 d FOT pruning volunteers as they prune young trees from the ground.  Partic
 ipants will also receive educational materials that provide more informatio
 n on basic pruning techniques\, how structural pruning can be used to impro
 ve tree resiliency\, and the importance of young tree care and a healthy ur
 ban forest. Make a difference in a few short hours by learning more about s
 hade tree pruning\, and practicing your new skills!</span><br></p><p><span>
 <b><u>Any questions?</u></b> Please check out the</span><span> </span><span
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> and d</span><span>on't he
 sitate to reach out to the Volunteer &amp\; Outreach team: </span><a href="
 mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u><u></u>dsoftrees
 .org</a><span>  We hope to prune with you soon!</span><br></p>
