DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><p>==========</p><p><b>Due to popular 
 interest\, this event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider an
 y other open event\, and thank you for your consideration!</p><p>==========
 </p><p>Let's plant trees together in inner NE Portland! Interested in recei
 ving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE
 </a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall
 ) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is wh
 at makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to
  sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We
  provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress fo
 r the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and 
 be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help g
 etting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the
  central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftr
 ees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a></b> if you're able t
 o help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;</p><p><b>This event will have a bike
  crew!</b>&nbsp\;The bike crew is now full\, and we're grateful for that ab
 undant interest.</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 
 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can v
 olunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://
 friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by t
 heir parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel 
 from the meeting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborh
 ood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportat
 ion</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carp
 ooling options. If this is a barrier to your participation\, please let us 
 know.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and 
 staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that
  all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those
  who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severe
 ly immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask throu
 gh the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not
  in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks 
 or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels u
 nwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions
  webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbs
 p\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following 
 neighborhoods: Irvington\, Sullivan's Gulch\, Grant Park\, Alameda\, Sabin\
 , Boise\, Eliot\, Humboldt\, King\, Concordia\, Piedmont\, Vernon\, and Woo
 dlawn.<br></p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;
 <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpag
 e</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Ga
 briel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to plan
 ting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with 
 the City of Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – thank you for you
 r longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><i>Friends of Trees continu
 es to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon 
