DESCRIPTION:<span><span>================<br><br>This event is now <b><u>ful
 l and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Thank you for your interest\, we hope you cons
 ider our <b>SE Portland event on November 13th </b>or <b>Oregon City on Nov
 ember 20th!</b><br><br>================</span></span><p><br><b>Have a picku
 p truck?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting 
 sites a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b
 ><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.or
 g/truck</a></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;</p><
 p><b>This event will have a bike crew!</b> Want to join the team planting t
 rees by bike? Sign up at <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/bike">ww
 w.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/bike</a></b>. Bikers with trailers and cargo bi
 kes are awesome but anyone with a bike is welcome to take part!&nbsp\;<br><
 br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer 
 with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their ow
 n and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/y
 outhwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian
 .</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting loc
 ation to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several m
 iles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike 
 or vehicle)\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If t
 his is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What 
 about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number 
 one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our e
 vents are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 12 and
  anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<
 b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\,
  respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, br
 inging your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will nee
 d\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of
  this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;fo
 r more details.</p><p>Please contact Jenny and Carey at <a href="mailto:vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a> if you h
 ave questions or need any further information. We look forward to seeing yo
 u out there!&nbsp\;</p><b><hr></b>This event is in partnership with the Cit
 y of Milwaukie.<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelin
 es and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at a
 ny point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and no
 tify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
