DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Gresham! Interested in receivi
 ng a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" tar
 get="_blank"><u><u>HERE</u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your hou
 sehold. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in th
 eir new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possibl
 e!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew
 . The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\,
  as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask tha
 t all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't 
 mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? 
 </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but there is still room a
 t this event!  Please simply show-up at 8:45am and sign-in when you arrive.
   See you there!<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getti
 ng these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the cen
 tral staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TP
 a00000IOB76&tfa_2189=Gresham%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0VPa0000042U
 2H&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20February%208\,%202025%20at%208:30%20am
 &tfa_2190=2025-02-08&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" targ
 et="_blank"><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></a></b> if you're able to help out
  in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 an
 d under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer
  on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftre
 es.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></a></u>
 </b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: 
 You will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the ne
 arby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transporta
 tion</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if other
 s in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Ques
 tions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/
 volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u
 ></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reac
 h Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_
 blank"><b><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></
 b></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===
 <br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" 
 target="_blank"><u>Portland General Electric</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /
 ></b><p><br></p>
