DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/
 crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Planting C</u></u></u></a><a href="h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="
 _blank"><u><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></u></a> are trained volunteers who are
  crucial to planting trees and leading small group at our community plantin
 g events. Friends of Trees cannot run these events without the support of t
 his valued position!  After your training\, we expect you to help lead a cr
 ew at 4 Saturday morning events Nov-April (select for events that fit your 
 schedule!).    <br><br><u>This is an In-Person training for new Crew Leader
 s in the Neighborhood Trees program.  Please note: trainees will need to ha
 ve completed the online training before they attend this session</u>.  The 
 online session will be sent to you and available for two weeks.<br><br>Trai
 nees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn about tree identific
 ation\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet the staff you'll b
 e working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="https://fr
 iendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><
 u><u><u>Planting Crew Leader webpage</u></u></u></a> or contact: <a href="m
 ailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u>volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0-213  We hope to work with you in
  this important role!
