CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to plant tr
 ees properly and lead groups of volunteers at more than 80 different planti
 ng events this planting season.  Friends of Trees is aiming to plant more t
 han 3\,000 street and yard trees in our award-winning Neighborhood Trees pr
 ogram.\n\nThe November 12th training is taking place in West Vancouver. We 
 are hosting another training Crew Leader training in Portland\, OR on Novem
 ber 5th\, if that works better for your schedule. Curriculum for each train
 ing is the same and once completed\, you will be able to volunteer at Neigh
 borhood Trees events throughout Portland\, Vancouver\, and Oregon City!\n\n
 The training is free (and includes lunch and a t-shirt!) but registration i
 s required.  <b>Register <a href="https://docs.google.com/a/friendsoftrees.
 org/forms/d/1qK5n4pqfzT_OtodhgCXj9HzzCcPmHMB3l2_UDuzGRIg/closedform">HERE</
 a> to train for this popular role.</b>  Spots are limited and this training
  will fill-up so register soon! Location is in SE Portland and will be incl
 uded with the information sent upon your registration.\n\nPlease contact Je
 nny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you need more information. We look forwar
 d to answering any questions you may have!\n\n<b>Thank you to RIGERT SHADE 
 TREES for generously sponsoring this training event.<b>\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Vancouver City Hall\, 415 W 6th St\, Vancouver\, WA 98660\, USA
