BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20221112T164500Z
DTEND:20221112T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260313T023243Z
UID:5f22jdrs9n5d2qhri651u34tk8@google.com
CREATED:20220829T162237Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>Let's plant trees togethe
 r in the neighborhoods on the North side of Oregon City!&nbsp\;</b>Interest
 ed in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get
 -a-tree/">HERE</a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of
  large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, a
 nd your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please a
 rrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting st
 arts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light
  breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers 
 dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirt
 y\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Register by f
 illing out <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000Vb
 lkT&tfa_2189=Oregon%20City%20neighborhood%20planting%20(North)&tfa_31=a0V5G
 00000UWj7y&tfa_45=Tree%20Planter\,%20%20at%20November%2012\,%202022%20at%20
 8:45%20am&tfa_2190=2022-11-12&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=off
 site">this quick form</a></b>.&nbsp\; Groups and individuals welcome! If yo
 ur group is more than 5 people\, please know you will be assigned to differ
 ent planting crews.<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help ge
 tting these young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the 
 central staging site. Please sign up at <b><u><a href="http://www.friendsof
 trees.org/truck">www.friendsoftrees.org/truck</a></u></b> if you're able to
  help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We 
 request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Yo
 uth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp
 \;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</
 a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private transpor
 tation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several planting s
 ites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b>We recommen
 d private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an 
 option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortabl
 e with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone carpooling with othe
 rs outside of their household wear a face mask\, and crack the windows of t
 he vehicle.&nbsp\; </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> tha
 t all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been ex
 posed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the even
 t.&nbsp\; We <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring an
 d wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physi
 cal distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</a></u></b>&
 nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Wher
 e will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the following neighborhoods: Ba
 rclay Hills\, Canemah\, McLoughlin\, Park Place\, Rivercrest\, and South En
 d.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a>
 </u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gab
 riel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"
 >volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting
  together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="
 https://portlandgeneral.com/"><u>PGE</u></a>.<br>===<br></p><b><hr></b><p>T
 his event is in partnership with the City of Oregon City.</p><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u></html-blob>
