DESCRIPTION:<b><br><hr><p></p></b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" id="ow9654" __is_owner="true">Planting 
 C</a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-le
 ader/">rew Leaders</a>&nbsp\;are trained volunteers who are crucial to plan
 ting trees and leading small group at our community planting events. Friend
 s of Trees can not run these events without the support of this valued posi
 tion! This training is for the Neighborhood Trees program where you'll plan
 t large-stock trees (6-10' tall) in city neighborhoods.<br><br><b><a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Learn m
 ore and register here</a></b> for this important position. Space limited.<b
 r><b><p></p></b><ul><li><b><u>What about Covid-19?</u></b>&nbsp\;We are req
 uiring all volunteers and staff are fully-vaccinated\, arrive at all events
  wearing a face masks (depending on the event it may be possible to remove 
 your mask after planting begins)\, and maintain 6' or more of physical spac
 e from folks outside of your household. We'll explain more at the training\
 , but also feel free to check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/v
 olunteer-faq/">Covid-19 &amp\; Volunteer FAQ page</a>&nbsp\;for more detail
 s.</li></ul><ul><li><b><u>A note on planting location and personal transpor
 tation</u>:</b>&nbsp\;You will be eligible to Crew Lead at plantings in the
  following cities: Beaverton\, Vancouver\, Portland (N\, NE\, SE\, E)\, Gre
 sham\, Milwaukie\, Oregon City\, and Wilsonville.  Due to Covid-19\, person
 al transportation is highly recommended-- we cannot guarantee that carpools
  will be available due to differing comfort levels of other FOT volunteers.
 </li></ul><b><p></p><hr><p></p></b>Ple<u></u>ase contact Jenny or Carey if 
 you need more information or have questions:&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a>. We look forw
 ard to working with you this planting season!
