DESCRIPTION:Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting
  trees properly and leading groups of volunteers at more than 25 different 
 planting events this coming planting season!&nbsp\; Friends of Trees is aim
 ing to plant more than 3\,000 street and yard trees in our award-winning Ne
 ighborhood Trees program\, and needs your help to make this possible!<br><b
 r>The November 10th training is taking place in Vancouver. We are hosting a
 nother training Crew Leader training in Portland\, OR on November <u></u>3r
 d\,<u></u> if that works better for your schedule. Curriculum for each trai
 ning is the same and once completed\, you will be able to volunteer at Neig
 hborhood Trees events throughout Portland\, Vancouver\, Beaverton\, Gresham
 \, and Oregon City!<br><br>The training is free (and includes lunch and a t
 -shirt!) but registration is required. Click <a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/portland-vancouver-crew-leader-training/" target="_blank">HERE</a> to
  register for this popular training.&nbsp\; Spots are limited and this trai
 ning will fill-up so <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/portland-vancouver
 -crew-leader-training/" target="_blank">register now! </a>Location is in SE
  Portland and will be included with the information sent upon your registra
 tion.<br><br>Please contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you need mo
 re information. We look forward to answering any questions you may have!<br
 ><br>&nbsp\;
