CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Overwhelmed by the choices? Let our Tree Matching Expert\, Jim 
 Gersbach help you find your "soil" mate. The right tree is out there\; let 
 us help you find it.\n\n\nJim will be helping neighbors find their perfect 
 tree on Thursday\, January 14th from 7 to 9 p.m. at Cerimon House (5131 NE 
 23rd Ave). The presentation is free\, and light refreshments will be provid
 ed.\n\n\nJim is a long-time Friends of Trees volunteer and will share infor
 mation\, photos and fun facts about the trees FOT is offering this year.  J
 im has an incredible range of knowledge about Portland's urban forest--from
  how different species tolerate our specific urban climate to what trees gr
 ow where across the city.  Further\, he has been inspired to travel far and
  wide to visit noteworthy trees across the country and beyond.\n\n\nHe is a
 lso the visionary behind the Ainsworth Linear Arboretum that runs for nearl
 y 2 miles along NE Ainsworth St. from MLK Blvd. to Fernhill Park.  As a lab
 or of love\, Jim has not only planted dozens of rare and unusual trees here
 \, but he has hand watered them through many a hot summers. \n\n\nThere is 
 no time like the present to order trees for the upcoming Friends of Trees P
 lanting Day in YOUR neighborhood! So\, log-in at FriendsOfTrees.org to sele
 ct and order your top picks as soon as possible! \n\n\nIf you need assistan
 ce in making a selection\, but cannot make this presentation\, give us a ca
 ll at 503-595-0212.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Cerimon House\, 5131 NE 23rd Ave\, Portland\, OR 97211\, United St
 ates
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Speed (Tree) Dating â Find your perfect tree match!
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
