CREATED:20210820T221238Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in SE Portland! Interested in rec
 eiving a tree? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HE
 RE</a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' ta
 ll) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is 
 what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am 
 to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. 
 We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteers dress 
 for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, an
 d be ready to have fun! </p><p><b>How do I register?&nbsp\;</b>Online regis
 tration is closed at this time. There is still room at this event\, please 
 simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</
 b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a fe
 w blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <b><a href="
 http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck">www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</a
 ></b> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Unde
 r age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a par
 ent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will
  need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver
 ">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b
 >Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to s
 everal planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbs
 p\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle
 )\, and will be unlikely able to provide carpooling options. If this is a b
 arrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What about Covi
 d-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priori
 ty at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are 
 fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 12 and anyone&nb
 sp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&n
 bsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6
 ' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your o
 wn water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cance
 l if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. 
 Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b
 >Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more detail
 s.</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?</b>&nbsp\;In the following n
 eighborhoods: Creston-Kenilworth\, Foster-Powell\, Mt Scott-Arleta\, Reed\,
  Brentwood Darlington\, Woodstock\, Eastmoreland\, Sellwood-Westmoreland\, 
 and Brooklyn</p><p>Please contact Jenny and Carey at <a href="mailto:volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a> if you have
  questions or need any further information. We look forward to seeing you o
 ut there!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Po
 rtland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – thank you for your longstanding
  commitment to planting trees!</p><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to foll
 ow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Aut
 hority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will can
 cel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><br><i><br></
 i><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https://wyldcanna.com
 /">WYLD</a>&nbsp\; &amp\; <a href="https://getchipdrop.com/">Chipdrop</a>!<
 br>===&nbsp\;<i><br></i>
