DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Out of an abundance of caution\, th
 is event is postponed due to continued frozen rain\, icy road conditions\, 
 and frozen ground. </b>Please stay safe.  We hope to see you at the Sat Apr
 il 6th Beaverton planting when we'll look forward to planting these trees i
 n South Beaverton!</p><p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees togethe
 r in the South Beaverton neighborhood! </b><span>Dozens of large (6-10' tal
 l) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is w
 hat makes this community planting possible!</span><br></p><p>Please arrive 
 by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts a
 t 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light break
 fast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress 
 for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, an
 d be ready to have fun!</p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 an
 d under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer
  on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org
 /youthwaiver"><u><u><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></a> sign
 ed by their parent/guardian.<p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will trav
 el from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighbor
 hood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bik
 e or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your sma
 ll planting crew are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>
 Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u
 ><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our tea
 m is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsof
 trees.org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></
 u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><
 p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Beaverton.</p>
