 , but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting cr
 ew are also comfortable with this. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyon
 e carpooling with others outside of their household wear a face mask\, and 
 crack the windows of the vehicle.&nbsp\; </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>
  We <u>require</u> that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling 
 unwell or have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 wit
 hin 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; We <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully
 -vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, a
 nd respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="htt
 ps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Question
 s webpage</a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\
 ;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>In the follo
 wing neighborhoods: Bella Vista\, Cascade Highlands\, Cascade Southeast\, F
 isher's Creek\, Fisher's Landing East\, Lewis and Clark Woods\, and Wildwoo
 d.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a>
 </u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gab
 riel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"
 >volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting
  together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City
  of Vancouver.</p><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>\n\nJoin with Google Mee
 t: https://meet.google.com/kuw-ouiu-osh\nOr dial: (US) +1 304-691-0182 PIN:
  398612870#\nMore phone numbers: https://tel.meet/kuw-ouiu-osh?pin=56955172
 74757&hs=7\n\nLearn more about Meet at: https://support.google.com/a/users/
 answer/9282720
