UID:2ruevn5vhed4fvpsgkqaauo83p@google.com
CREATED:20220321T193438Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p>============</p><p><b
 >Thanks to popular support\, this planting is <u>full and closed</u></b>.&n
 bsp\; Weren't able to register already? Please consider any future event on
  the calendar here - thank you for your consideration!</p><p>============</
 p><p>Celebrate Beaverton Arbor Day by planting trees! Dozens of large (6-10
 ' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help
  is what makes this community planting possible!<br></p><p>Please arrive by
  8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 
 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. We ask that all volunteer
 s dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting di
 rty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request
  that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 
 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u>youth waiver form</u></a>
 </b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b>What about Covid-1
 9?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority 
 at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are ful
 ly-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as chi
 ldren younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,<
 /b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, resp
 ect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring y
 our own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and 
 cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this ev
 ent. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq
 /"><u><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></u></a>&nbsp\;for
  more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nb
 sp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team
  is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny 
 at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><b>volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</b></u></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!
 &nbsp\;</p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Beav
 erton -- thank you for your longstanding commitment to community tree-plant
 ing!</p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommen
 dations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we fee
 l it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunt
 eers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><br><u></u><i><
 br></i><u></u><br><u></u>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors&nbsp\;<a hr
 ef="https://www.hamptonlumber.com/" id="ow4879" __is_owner="true"><u>Hampto
 n Lumber</u></a>&nbsp\;&amp\; <a href="http://www.tree-source.net/" id="ow4
 895" __is_owner="true">Rigert Shade Trees</a>!<br>===<i><br></i><u></u></ht
 ml-blob>
