DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=========</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this eve
 nt is <u>full and closed</u>.  </b>Please consider any available future eve
 nt -- we hope to plant with you soon!</p><p><b>=========</b></p><p><b>Let's
  plant trees together in Beaverton! </b><span>Dozens of large (6-10' tall) 
 trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what
  makes this community planting possible!</span><br></p><p>Please note: this
  is <u>a rare afternoon planting</u>. Arrive by 11:45am to sign-in and be a
 ssigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 12:00pm. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/h
 ot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturd
 y shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><
 p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a 
 parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will ne
 ed to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><b><u>yo
 uth waiver form</u></b></u></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Q
 uestions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vol
 unteer-faq/"><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></a>. 
  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@f
 riendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u><
 /u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr />
 <p></p><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Beaverton.</p>
