CREATED:20240110T171102Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>*********</b></p><p>Originally scheduled for Jan 13th\, t
 his event was postponed due to inclement weather. <b>Please sign-up to help
  these trees get planted today\, Jan 27th -- help sincerely needed!</b></p>
 <p><b>*********</b></p><p><b>Let's plant trees together in Central Vancouve
 r! </b>Interested in receiving a tree? Click <a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/get-a-tree/"><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></a> to purchase 
 a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready
  for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this communi
 ty planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assig
 ned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, too
 ls\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot ch
 ocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy sho
 es/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>
 How do I register? </b>Online registration is closed but more help is neede
 d\, please simply show up and sign in when you arrive. Groups and individua
 ls welcome! If your group is more than 5 people\, please know you will be a
 ssigned to different planting crews.<b><br></b></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><
 span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian. 
  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <
 /span><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><b><u>youth 
 waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></a><span> signed by their parent/guardian.<
 /span><br></p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting thes
 e young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central st
 aging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa000005
 vwNl&tfa_2189=Central-East%20Vancouver%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0V
 Pa000001StNZ&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20January%2027\,%202024%20at%2
 08:30%20am&tfa_2190=2024-01-27&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=off
 site"><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></a></b> if you're able to 
 help out in this key role. </p><p><b>Private transportation</b><span>: You 
 will travel from the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby
  neighborhood (up to several miles). </span><b>We recommend private transpo
 rtation</b><span> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool
  if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with this. </sp
 an><br></p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In the following ne
 ighborhoods: Burton Ridge\, DuBois Park\, Ellsworth Springs\, Evergreen Hig
 hlands\, Father Blanchet Park\, Forest Ridge\, Marrion\, North Garrison Hei
 ghts\, Northcrest\, Northwood\, Oakbrook\, Old Evergreen Hwy\, and Vancouve
 r Heights.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpag
 e</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reac
 h us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>
 volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forwar
 d to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This event is in
  partnership with the City of Vancouver.</p>
