DESCRIPTION:<p>==========</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is 
 <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any of our other open events --
  we hope to work with you soon!</p><p>==========</p><p>Let's plant trees to
 gether in Wilsonville!  Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href
 ="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your hou
 sehold. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in th
 eir new homes\, and your help is what makes this community planting possibl
 e!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew
 . The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\,
  as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask tha
 t all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't 
 mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck
 ?</b> We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a
  few blocks away from the central staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfa
 forms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000qajag&tfa_2189=Wilsonville%20neighborhoo
 d%20planting\,%20Wilsonville&tfa_31=a0VPa000008zJaF&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,
 %20%20at%20April%204\,%202026%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2026-04-04&tfa_49=4
 .5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> if y
 ou're able to help in this key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request
  that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and ol
 der can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="ht
 tp://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/
 guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the mee
 ting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to sev
 eral miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\,
  but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting cre
 w are also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease c
 heck out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to
  assist! <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u
 >g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 W
 e look forward to working together soon!<br></p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to o
 ur event sponsor\, <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><
 u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p>
 <b><hr /></b><p></p><p>This event in partnership with City of Wilsonville.<
 /p>
