DESCRIPTION:[<b>Update: Despite stormy conditions\, this planting will be c
 ontinuing as planned.</b>  Please make the best decision to volunteer based
  on your comfort and travel situation.  We will still be meeting at Upper F
 anno -- and look forward to working with you soon!]\n\nJoin us at the corne
 r of SW Black Bird Dr. and SW Siskin Terrace to plant 50 new street trees. 
 Look for Friends of Trees A frames to help guide you to the meeting locatio
 n.\n\nPlease arrive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some hot coffee 
 and breakfast treats.  The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide g
 loves and tools\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather 
 and wearing sturdy shoes.\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs 
 are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSV
 Ps are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simp
 ly show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny & Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have q
 uestions or need any further information.\n\nWe look forward to seeing you 
 out there!\n\n<b>Thank you to CHIPOTLE for generously sponsoring this plant
 ing event.<b>\n\n\n
