DESCRIPTION:<p>=====================</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, thi
 s event is <u>full and closed for planters</u></b>. However\, we still need
  <u>truck drivers</u> to chauffer trees to their new homes. More info below
 . Happy Earth Month &lt\;3</p><p>======================</p><p><br></p><p>Le
 t's plant trees together in the Northgate neighborhood and D Street Park in
  NE Salem! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>HERE</u></u></u></
 u></a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10
 ' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help
  is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:4
 5am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00
 am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast s
 nacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for th
 e weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be r
 eady to have fun!</p><p><b>D Street Park:</b> this event was originally sch
 eduled on 2/15/25 and was postponed due to snowy weather.  There will be so
 me planting crews that will head ~2.5 miles to plant at this park instead o
 f planting in the Northgate neighborhood.</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b>
  We need your help getting these young trees to their planting sites a few 
 blocks away from the central staging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms
 .com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000IOB7K&tfa_2189=Northgate%20neighborhood%20pla
 nting&tfa_31=a0VPa0000042XCH&tfa_45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20April%2012\,
 %202025%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2025-04-12&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20
 FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></a>
 </b> if you're able to help out in this key role. <br><br><b>Under age 18?<
 /b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Y
 outh 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b>
 <u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u
 ><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/gu
 ardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: <span> </span><span>Initial pa
 rking will be available at Chemeketa Community College Winema and</span><sp
 an> </span><span>Early College High School. </span><span>You will travel fr
 om the meeting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood 
 (up to 1 mile). </span><b>We recommend private transportation</b><span> (bi
 ke or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to carpool if others in your sm
 all planting crew are also comfortable with this.</span></p><p><b>Questions
 ?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assis
 t!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftree
 s.org" target="_blank"><b><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.
 org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></b></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward
  to planting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor
 s <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/">PGE</a> &amp\; <a href="https://ww
 w.nwnatural.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>NW Natural</u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is i
 n partnership with the City of Salem.</p>
