DTSTART:20230128T170000Z
DTEND:20230128T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260313T023243Z
UID:61kff3phpuhr0fu3mmub5nki6p@google.com
CREATED:20221118T182042Z
DESCRIPTION:=====<br><b>Due to fabulous community interest\, this event is 
 now <u>full and closed</u>. </b><br><br>=====<br><br><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u>Did you know that proper structural pruning when a tree is 
 young is an effective tool to help mitigate major tree failures from wind a
 nd ice storms</u>?  A few strategic pruning cuts can help a young tree live
  a long and health life in our urban environment!<p>Friends of Trees is off
 ering a free young-tree structural pruning workshop.  This completely outdo
 ors workshop will teach you how to identify pruning needs\, how and when to
  prune trees\, how to use different tools (no chainsaws though!)\, and more
 .</p><p><b><u>"What can I expect from the workshop?</u></b><span>" Particip
 ants will learn from and practice alongside FOT staff and experienced FOT p
 runing volunteers as they prune young trees near the park (South End/Riverc
 rest neighborhoods). You don't need to live in these neighborhoods to come 
 learn! Participants will also receive educational materials that provide mo
 re information on basic pruning techniques\, how structural pruning can be 
 used to improve tree resiliency\, and the importance of young tree care and
  a healthy urban forest. Make a difference in a few short hours by learning
  more about shade tree pruning\, and practicing your new skills!</span><br>
 </p><p><b><u>Event safety:</u></b> Friends of Trees requires<span> </span><
 span>that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have
  been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of 
 the event. See our safety recommendations and other volunteering informatio
 n on the</span><span> </span><b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Ask
 ed Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a
 ></u></b><span>.</span></p>Any questions? Please don't hesitate to reach ou
 t to the Volunteer &amp\; Outreach team: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org">volunteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a>  We hope to prune with 
 you soon!<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230123T222858Z
LOCATION:Chapin Park\, 340 Warner Parrott Rd\, Oregon City\, OR 97045\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:FULL - Tree Pruning Workshop (Oregon City\, OR)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
