UID:3smn2tunf1tajplortc3nacj9r@google.com
CREATED:20230829T132216Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event
  is <u>full and closed</u>.  </b>Please consider our other NE Portland plan
 ting at Gateway Green instead\, starting at 9:45am.  We hope to plant with 
 you soon!</p><p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Let's pla</b><b>nt trees together i
 n NE Portland!</b> Interested in receiving a tree? Click <a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u><u><u><b><u>HERE</u></b></u></u></u></a> 
 to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees w
 ill be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes 
 this community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in 
 and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide 
 gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffe
 e/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wea
 r sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fu
 n!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these young 
 trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging si
 te.</p><p><b>Want to plant by bike?</b> This event will have a bike-powered
  crew. Bring your bike\, helmet\, and a bike trailer (if you have one).</p>
 <p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a
  parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will n
 eed to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><
 b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></u></u></a> signed by their parent/guard
 ian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting 
 location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several 
 miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but 
 there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are
  also comfortable with this. </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? <
 /b>In the neighborhoods of Cully and Sumner.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pleas
 e check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><
 u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is 
 also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u
 ></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you
  to our event sponsors <a href="https://wyldcanna.com/"><u>WYLD</u></a> &am
 p\; <a href="https://laughingplanet.com/">Laughing Planet</a>.</p><p>===</p
 ><p></p><hr /><p></p><p>This planting is part of Clean Air Canopy\, a coali
 tion effort to help ensure equitable access to clean air and a healthy envi
 ronment for Northeast Portland community members. When a NE Portland glass 
 plant reached a settlement with Oregon DEQ related to compliance with their
  air quality permit\, a portion of the penalty contributed funds to approve
 d local environmental projects\, including planting trees. The trees plante
 d at this community event will bring long-term human and environmental heal
 th benefits to the area\, critical to our environmental justice efforts. Pa
 rtner groups include Verde\, Cully Association of Neighbors\, Cully Air Act
 ion Team\, and Friends of Trees.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240202T155305Z
