DESCRIPTION:After a weather setback in January\, Friends of Trees is excite
 d to reschedule this event and bring trees to the homes of Central Vancouve
 r! \n\n*We'll be planting in the neighborhoods of Bagley Downs\, Burton Rid
 ge\, Ellsworth Springs\, Evergreen Highlands\, Father Blanchet Park\, Duboi
 s Park\, Forest Ridge\, Marrion\, Meadow Homes\, Northcrest\, Northwood\, N
 orth Garrison Heights\, Oakbrook\, Ogden\, South Cliff\, Vancouver Heights\
 , and VanMall.\n\nPlease arrive to the staging site by 8:45am to enjoy some
  hot coffee and breakfast treats.  The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. 
 We provide gloves and tools\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for 
 the weather and wearing sturdy shoes.  Our neighborhood volunteers will als
 o provide a potluck lunch for all volunteers after the planting is complete
 !\n\nPlease contact our Volunteer Team at volunteer[at]friendsoftrees.org o
 r (503) 595-0213 if you have questions or need any further information.\n\n
 We look forward to seeing you out there!
