CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Overwhelmed by the choices? Let our Tree Matching Expert\, Jim 
 Gersbach help you find your "soil" mate. The right tree is out there\, let 
 us help you find it.\n\nJim will be helping Portland and Vancouver neighbor
 s find their perfect tree on Tuesday\, December 10th from 7 to 9 p.m. at th
 e Kenton Firehouse (8105 N Brandon Ave). The presentation is free\, and lig
 ht refreshments will be provided.\n \nJim is a long-time Friends of Trees v
 olunteer and will share information\, photos and fun facts about the trees 
 FOT is offering this year.  Jim has an incredible range of knowledge about 
 Portland's urban forest--from how different species tolerate our specific u
 rban climate to what trees grow where across the city.  Further\, he has be
 en inspired to travel far and wide to visit noteworthy trees across the cou
 ntry and beyond.\n\nHe is also the visionary behind the Ainsworth Linear Ar
 boretum that runs for nearly 2 miles along NE Ainsworth St. from MLK Blvd. 
 to Fernhill Park.  As a labor of love\, Jim has not only planted dozens of 
 rare and unusual trees here\, but he has hand watered them through many a h
 ot summers.\n  \nThere is no time like the present to order trees for the u
 pcoming Friends of Trees Planting Day in YOUR neighborhood!  \n\nYour order
  deadline is coming up quick\, so log-in at FriendsOfTrees.org to select an
 d order your top picks as soon as possible!\n  \nIf you need assistance in 
 making a selection\, but cannot make this presentation\, give us a call at 
 503-595-0212.\n \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Kenton Firehouse (8105 N Brandon Ave)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Speed (Tree) Dating â Find your perfect tree match! 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
