CREATED:20240814T192934Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Let's plant trees together in Milwaukie! Interested in recei
 ving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" t
 arget="_blank">HERE</a></u></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Doze
 ns of large (6-10' tall) trees will be ready for planting in their new home
 s\, and your help is what makes this community planting possible!</p><p>Ple
 ase arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planti
 ng starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as 
 light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunt
 eers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting
  dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Onlin<u>
 </u><u></u>e registration has closed at this time\, but there is still room
  at this event\, please simply <u>show up at 8:45am</u> and sign-in when yo
 u arrive.</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting these
  young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central sta
 ging site. <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000IO
 B6n&tfa_2189=Milwaukie%20neighborhood%20planting&tfa_31=a0VPa0000042U1N&tfa
 _45=Truck%20Driver\,%20%20at%20October%2026\,%202024%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2
 190=2024-10-26&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_b
 lank">Please sign up</a></b> if you're able to help out in this key role. <
 /p><p><b>Want to plant by bike?</b> Online registration has closed\, just s
 imply show up and let us know you want to plant by bike.<br><br><b>Under ag
 e 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardi
 an.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us
  a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank">yo
 uth waiver form</a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Priva
 te transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few p
 lanting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recom
 mend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an opt
 ion to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable w
 ith this.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank">Volunteer FAQ webpag
 e</a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and J
 enny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volun
 teer@friendsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting to
 gether soon!<br></p><br><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with t
 he City of Milwaukie.</p>
