DESCRIPTION:<br>=============<br><br>Thank you for your interest in this ev
 ent!&nbsp\; <u>Our SE Vancouver planting is now <b>full and closed</b> to v
 olunteer registration</u>.&nbsp\; Please consider any of our other open eve
 nts\, including our next Clark County planting on Sat Dec 8th!<br><br>=====
 ========<u><br></u><i>Neighborhoods include: Bella Vista\, Cascade Highland
 s\, Cascade Southeast\, Fisher's Creek\, Fisher's Landing East\, Lewis and 
 Clark Woods\, and Wildwood.<br></i><br>Please arrive by 12:15pm to sign-in 
 and enjoy a warm lunch before we get started planting. The planting starts 
 promptly at 12:30pm. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you 
 need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or b
 oots â and be ready to have fun!&nbsp\;<br>&nbsp\;<br><b>Have a pickup tr
 uck? </b>We need your help getting these young trees to their planting site
 s a few blocks away from the central staging site. Please sign up at <a hre
 f="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck" target="_blank">www.friendsoftrees.
 org/truck</a> if you're able to help us out in this key role. <br><br><b>Un
 der age 18?</b> A signed <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/
 pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for
  you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompa
 nied by an adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at 503-59
 5-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org </a>if you have questions or need any further inf
 ormation. We look forward to seeing you out there!
