DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u>
 </u><p><b>In celebration of Milwaukie's Arbor Day\, let's plant trees toget
 her across Milwaukie neighborhoods!&nbsp\;</b>Interested in receiving a tre
 e? Click <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/">HERE</a></u
 ></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) t
 rees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what 
 makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to s
 ign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We p
 rovide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks an
 d coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weathe
 r\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to 
 have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at
  this point\, but there is still room available. Please simply show up!&nbs
 p\;&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting the
 se young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central s
 taging site. Please sign up at <u style=""><a href="http://www.friendsoftre
 es.org/truck" id="ow610" __is_owner="true" style="">www.friendsoftrees.org/
 truck</a></u> if you're able to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;</p><p>
 <b>Ride your bike?</b> There will be a bike planting crew at this event.  L
 earn more and sign-up for the bike crew: <a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/bike"><u>https://friendsoftrees.org/bike</u></a></p><p><b>Under age 18?</
 b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardia
 n.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to ha
 nd us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth w
 aiver form</a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Priv
 ate transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to severa
 l planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles).&nbsp\;<b
 >We recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp\;(bike or vehicle)\, but ther
 e may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting crew are als
 o comfortable with this. <u>Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone carpo
 oling with others outside of their household wear a face mask\, and crack t
 he windows of the vehicle</u>.&nbsp\; </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We
  <u>require</u> that people cancel their participation if you are feeling u
 nwell or have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 with
 in 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; We <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-
 vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, an
 d respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions
  webpage</a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;
 &nbsp\;</p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted?&nbsp\;</b>Trees will be
  planted in ALL Milwaukie neighborhoods.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<
 /b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vol
 unteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also hap
 py to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href
 ="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u>
 </b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This
  event is in partnership with the City of Milwaukie.</p><p><br></p><p>===<b
 r>Thank you to our event sponsors&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.yachak.com/"><
 u>Yachak</u></a>\,&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.newseasonsmarket.com/">New Se
 asons Market</a>&nbsp\;&amp\; <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/">PGE</a
 ><br>===<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></h
 tml-blob>
