DESCRIPTION:<p>========</p><p><b>Thanks to popular interest\, this event is
  <u>full and closed</u></b>.  Please consider any other open event -- we ho
 pe to plant with you soon!</p><p>========</p><p>Let's plant trees together 
 in Gresham! Interested in receiving a tree? Click <b><u><a href="https://fr
 iendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/" target="_blank"><u>HERE</u></a></u></b> to pu
 rchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) trees will b
 e ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what makes this 
 community planting possible!</p><p>Please arrive by 11:45am to sign-in and 
 be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 12:00pm. We provide glo
 ves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/t
 ea/hot chocolate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear s
 turdy shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!<
 /p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer wit
 h a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and wil
 l need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" t
 arget="_blank"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/
 guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the mee
 ting location to a few planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to sev
 eral miles). <b>We recommend private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\,
  but there may be an option to carpool if others in your small planting cre
 w are also comfortable with this.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out
  our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_bla
 nk"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to as
 sist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoft
 rees.org" target="_blank"><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></a>\, 
 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr /><
 /b><p>This event made possible through a grant from the USDA Forest Service
 . This institution is an equal opportunity provider.<br></p>
