CREATED:20230223T190145Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Due to unexpected wintry conditions\, Friends of Trees was f
 orced to delay the originally scheduled planting event on Feb 25th.  <b>Now
  we need your support <u>to plant 200 trees</u> in Westside Vancouver neigh
 borhoods on our rescheduled date: March 4th!</b></p><p><span>Please arrive 
 by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts a
 t 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as well as light break
 fast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. Following the event there will be
  a warm potluck lunch provided by the hosting neighborhood groups. We ask t
 hat all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don'
 t mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</span><br></p><p><b>How do
  I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but there is
  still room at this event!  Please simply show-up at 8:45am and sign-in whe
 n you arrive!</p><p><b>Have a pickup truck?</b> We need your help getting t
 hese young trees to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central
  staging site. Please sign up at <b><u><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.o
 rg/truck"><u>www.friendsoftrees.org/truck</u></a></u></b> if you're able to
  help out in this key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><span> We request th
 at youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older
  can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a </span><b><u><a href
 ="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></u></
 b><span> signed by their parent/guardian.</span><br></p><p><b>Private trans
 portation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to several plantin
 g sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recommend p
 rivate transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an option to
  carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable with th
 is. Please note: FOT is requiring that anyone carpooling with others outsid
 e of their household wear a face mask\, and crack the windows of the vehicl
 e.  </p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> that all people at
  our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to someon
 e who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.  For safety 
 recommendations and more\, please see our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u
 ></a></u></b>.        </p><p><b>Where will these trees be planted? </b>In t
 he following neighborhoods:  Arnada\, Carter Park\, Central Park\, Esther S
 hort\, Fruit Valley\, Hough\, Hudson's Bay\, Lincoln\, Northwest\, Rose Vil
 lage\, and Shumway.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a 
 href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</
 u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel a
 nd Jenny at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u>voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org</u></a></u></b> We look forward to planting together s
 oon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://wyldcanna
 .com/"><u><u><u><u>Wyld</u></u></u></u></a>.<br>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This
  event is in partnership with the City of Vancouver.<br></p>\n\nJoin with G
 oogle Meet: https://meet.google.com/wjz-edty-tmu\nOr dial: (US) +1 929-287-
 3718 PIN: 579329075#\nMore phone numbers: https://tel.meet/wjz-edty-tmu?pin
 =9258273977636&hs=7\n\nLearn more about Meet at: https://support.google.com
 /a/users/answer/9282720
