CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20190808T153327Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive to the Hinson Memorial Church at 8:45am for regis
 tration\, coffee\, and breakfast pastries. Enter the main building on Salmo
 n St at the "elevator" entrance sign\, and follow the FOT A-frames.\n\n<b>D
 ue to popular demand\, this training is now full and closed.</b>.  Please c
 onsider registering for this same training held Sat\, May 21st in Vancouver
 \, WA!\n\nSummer inspectors are always one of our most popular volunteers r
 oles. Why? These trained volunteers learn how to assess the health of newly
  planted street and yard trees and give homeowners watering and mulching ti
 ps. Each inspector checks on his or her assigned trees twice during the sum
 mer (once in June and once in August). Being a summer inspector gives you a
  chance to meet your neighbors and to help them take care of their trees du
 ring the critical first summer after planting. Plus\, you get to stroll aro
 und Portland's beautiful neighborhoods in the summer sun at your own leisur
 e. Not a bad way to do good work!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at 503-5
 95-0213 or Volunteer@FriendsofTrees.org if you have any questions or need m
 ore information. We look forward to seeing you there!
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T155127Z
LOCATION:Hinson Memorial Church\, 1137 SE 20th Ave\, Portland\, OR 97214
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Neighborhood Trees Summer Inspector Training (SE Portland)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
