DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p>=======</p><p>
 <b>Due to popular interest\, this event is now <u>full and closed for addit
 ional tree planters</u></b>. However\, we still need the following voluntee
 r roles:&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p></p><ul><li>Truck Driver&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<ul><li>
 <b>Have a pickup truck?</b>&nbsp\;We need your help getting these young tre
 es to their planting sites a few blocks away from the central staging site.
  Please sign up at&nbsp\;<b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/truck"><
 u><u>www.friendsoftr<u></u>ees.org/truck</u></u></a></b>&nbsp\;if you're ab
 le to help us out in this key role.&nbsp\;</li></ul></li><li>Crew Leaders &
 amp\; Assistant Crew Leaders&nbsp\;<ul><li>Email <a href="mailto:volunteer@
 friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you are available a
 nd an already trained Crew Leader</li></ul></li></ul><p></p><p>=======</p><
 p>Let's plant trees together in West Portland! Interested in receiving a tr
 ee? Click <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/get-a-tree/"><u>HERE</u></
 a></b> to purchase a tree for your household. Dozens of large (6-10' tall) 
 trees will be ready for planting in their new homes\, and your help is what
  makes this community planting possible!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to 
 sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We 
 provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. Dress for the weather\, wear sturdy 
 shoes/boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p>
 <br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer
  with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their o
 wn and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/
 youthwaiver"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/
 guardian.</p><p><b>Private transportation</b>: You will travel from the mee
 ting location to several planting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to s
 everal miles).&nbsp\;<b>We highly recommend private transportation</b>&nbsp
 \;(bike or vehicle)\, and will be unable to provide carpooling options. If 
 this is a barrier to your participation\, please let us know.</p><p><b>What
  about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number
  one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our 
 events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible
 \, such as children younger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face ma
 sk through the event introductions\, and cancel if anyone in your household
  feels unwell prior to the event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions 
 webpage</b></u></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&
 nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </u></a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach
  Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftr
 ees.org"><u><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></u></a>&nbsp\;We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partner
 ship with the City of Portland’s Bureau of Environmental Services – thank y
 ou for your longstanding commitment to planting trees!</p><p><i>Friends of 
 Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CD
 C and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to ho
 st events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-regis
 tered.</i><br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https:
 //www.laika.com/"><u>Laika Studios</u></a>&nbsp\;&amp\; <a href="https://2t
 ownsciderhouse.com/">2 Towns Ciderhouse</a>!<br>===<i><br></i></p><p><i><br
 ></i></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
