 021\,%202026%20at%208:30%20am&tfa_2190=2026-02-21&tfa_49=4.5&tfa_886=Standa
 rd%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u>Please sign up</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></a></b> if you're able to help in this key role. </p><p><b>Under age 18
 ?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian. 
  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <
 b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u>
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Private
  transportation</b>: You will travel from the meeting location to a few pla
 nting sites in the nearby neighborhood (up to several miles). <b>We recomme
 nd private transportation</b> (bike or vehicle)\, but there may be an optio
 n to carpool if others in your small planting crew are also comfortable wit
 h this. </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
