DESCRIPTION:Neighborhood Coordinators (NC) are essential to making a Friend
 s of Trees' neighborhood tree planting event possible!  Becoming an NC is a
 n excellent way to be a leader in your neighborhood and to make it a more b
 eautiful and healthy place to live.  We'll train you in all aspects of this
  role and will support you throughout the planting season as you help your 
 neighbors order trees and you organize the logistics of planting day.  No e
 xperience is necessary!\n\nThe training will take place at Portland Communi
 ty College's Cascade Campus in the Terrell Hall 122 Auditorium from 9am - 1
 2pm.  Coffee and breakfast treats will be provided.\n\nPlease contact Jesse
  Batty at JesseB@FriendsofTrees.org or 503-282-8846\, ext. 25 if you'd like
  to sign up for the training or if you have additional questions.
